          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just played the ultimate card. He is God. He literally has nothing left to achieve in all three worlds — no promotion pending, no KRA left, no bucket list item unchecked. And yet? Varta eva ca karmaṇi — He still works. This is the CEO who already has more money than he can spend in ten lifetimes but still shows up at 8 AM because the company matters. Except this CEO created the company, the employees, the market, and the laws of physics governing the building. If the Supreme Being himself does not retire and put his feet up, what excuse do you have? This verse destroys every 'I have arrived, so I can stop now' mindset. The highest state is not inaction. It is action without need. That is grace in motion."
