          modernInterpretation: "THIS. This is the verse you need tattooed on your forehead. Krishna just said the most powerful self-help line in the history of humanity — 5,000 years before Tony Robbins, before Atomic Habits, before every motivational Instagram page. YOUR MIND IS YOUR BEST FRIEND AND YOUR WORST ENEMY. Nobody else. Not your toxic ex. Not your micromanaging boss. Not the government. Not the economy. Not the algorithm. YOUR OWN MIND. Think about it — who tells you that you are not good enough? Your mind. Who keeps you scrolling Instagram at 2 AM comparing yourself to strangers? Your mind. Who replays that embarrassing thing you said in 2014 at a party? Your mind. Who convinces you to skip the gym, eat the third slice of cake, procrastinate on the project, ghost that person, stay in that toxic situation? YOUR. MIND. But also — who gets you out of bed when everything feels hopeless? Your mind. Who tells you 'one more try'? Your mind. Who dreams, creates, loves, builds, perseveres? Your mind. Same device, two modes. Your mind is like a smartphone — it can be used to build a business or to waste 6 hours watching reels. The phone is not good or bad. How you USE it determines everything. Krishna says — 'uddharet atmanam' — LIFT YOURSELF UP. No one is coming to save you. No guru, no government scheme, no lottery ticket. You have to be your own rescue team. And the first rescue mission? Rescuing yourself FROM yourself. From your own laziness, your own excuses, your own self-pity. Stop waiting for external validation. Stop waiting for someone to believe in you. Believe in yourself first. Be your own bandhu. Because if YOU become your own enemy, no army in the world can protect you from the destruction that follows."
