          modernInterpretation: "Krishna saves the most mind-bending claim for last in this sequence. 'Bījam sarva-bhūtānām' — I am the SEED of all beings. Not a seed. THE seed. The ETERNAL seed. Sanātanam. Think about what a seed is. It is potential. Pure, compressed, waiting potential. An entire banyan tree — with its hanging roots and massive canopy that shelters an entire village — sits inside a seed smaller than your fingernail. The entire universe, with its billions of galaxies and its Zomato delivery partners and its WhatsApp groups and its Bangalore traffic jams — all of it was once a seed. And that seed is Krishna. But the real knockout punch is what follows: 'buddhir buddhimatām asmi' — I am the INTELLIGENCE of the intelligent. Not 'I gave intelligence to intelligent people.' I AM their intelligence. That IIT topper who everyone celebrates? The intelligence that cracked the exam is not THEIRS. It is Krishna expressing Himself through them. That startup founder who had the breakthrough idea at 2 AM? That flash of insight was not their brain being clever — it was Krishna showing up as cleverness. This is simultaneously the most humbling and most liberating thing you will ever hear. Humbling because your greatest achievement was never really YOURS. Liberating because your greatest failure was never really yours either. You are an instrument. A flute. And the music — the intelligence, the splendor, the brilliance — is the BREATH of the divine moving through you. 'Tejas tejasvinām' — the splendor of the splendid. Every time you see someone and think 'Wow, there is something ABOUT that person' — that something is not the person. That something is the thread. That something is the taste in the water, the light in the sun, the fragrance after rain. That something is Krishna. Hiding in plain sight. In everything. In everyone. In YOU."
