          modernInterpretation: "This is the verse where Krishna basically invents the concept of a PLATFORM without being the CONTENT. Think of it this way: YouTube hosts every video — spiritual lectures, cat compilations, conspiracy theories, ASMR cooking, and absolute garbage. ALL of it exists ON YouTube. But YouTube is not DEFINED by any single video. The platform is beyond the content. Krishna is saying the exact same thing. Sattva, rajas, tamas — goodness, passion, ignorance — the morning raga you listen to while doing yoga, the road rage you feel in Bangalore traffic, the laziness that makes you skip the gym for the fourteenth consecutive Monday — ALL of these come from Him. He is the source. But here is the MIND-BENDING part: 'I am not in them; they are in Me.' The ocean contains every wave, but no single wave contains the ocean. Your WhatsApp has every chat — the spiritual group, the office gossip group, the family drama group — but YOU are not defined by any single group. You CONTAIN them. This is Krishna's way of saying: 'I created the game, I created the rules, I created every possible move — but I am not TRAPPED in the game. I am the one who can close the app.' This has massive implications. It means the universe with all its chaos, beauty, cruelty, and kindness is WITHIN the Divine — but the Divine is not limited by it. Your Netflix account has comedies, tragedies, and horror — but YOUR account is not a comedy or a tragedy. It is just the space where all of it plays. God is the SCREEN, not the movie."
