          modernInterpretation: "THIS is the verse that explains why eight billion people are walking around on this planet and almost nobody has a CLUE what is actually going on. Krishna is saying: the entire world is caught in a three-flavored HYPNOSIS — sattva, rajas, and tamas — and because of this triple spell, nobody can see the One who is BEHIND it all. Think of it as the ultimate Netflix binge. Sattva is when you are watching a beautiful documentary about the ocean and feeling all spiritual and evolved. Rajas is when you are fourteen episodes deep into a thriller at 3 AM, heart pounding, unable to stop. Tamas is when you have been watching garbage reality TV for six hours and you cannot even remember your own name. In ALL THREE CASES, you have forgotten that you are the PERSON sitting on the couch. You have become so absorbed in the CONTENT that you have forgotten you are the viewer. That is mohitam — delusion. And it is not just the tamasic people who are deluded. The sattvic person who is PROUD of being sattvic? Also deluded. The rajasic hustler who thinks grinding 18 hours a day will fill the void? Deluded. The tamasic couch potato? Obviously deluded. ALL THREE are screens within the same cinema hall, and nobody is looking at who OWNS the cinema. This is why your IIT-topper friend who earns 50 lakhs is still anxious. This is why the yoga teacher who posts sunrise photos is still comparing follower counts. This is why the retired uncle who watches news all day is still angry. Sattva, rajas, tamas — different FLAVORS of the same forgetting. The one who sees BEYOND all three flavors, who recognizes the imperishable consciousness behind the dance of the gunas — that one alone truly SEES. Everyone else is just watching a very convincing movie and thinking it is real."
