          translation: "This divine maya of Mine, consisting of the three gunas, is very difficult to overcome. But those who surrender unto Me alone cross beyond this illusion.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just gave you the BAD NEWS and the GOOD NEWS in the same breath. Bad news: Maya is DIVINE. It is not some cheap trick. It is not a bug in the system — it is a FEATURE. And it is almost impossible to beat. Good news: there is exactly ONE cheat code, and it is SURRENDER. Let me explain why maya is duratyayā — practically impossible to cross. Maya is not just ignorance. It is the most sophisticated illusion ever created. It is so good that it makes you think YOU are the one in control. That is its genius. A regular illusion, you eventually figure out — like a magic show, you know it is tricks. But maya? Maya makes you think there IS no illusion. That is NEXT LEVEL. It is like being inside a dream where you do not know you are dreaming. You are fighting, loving, crying, winning — all inside the dream — and it feels COMPLETELY real. Every startup founder who thinks THIS funding round will finally make them happy — maya. Every person refreshing LinkedIn hoping for validation — maya. Every Instagram filter that makes you forget what your actual face looks like — maya. Every arranged marriage biodata that says 'simple living, high thinking' when the person actually wants a 3BHK in Bandra — MAYA. And the harder you TRY to escape it on your own, the deeper you sink. Because the one who is trying to escape? That is ALSO maya. It is like trying to use your hands to lift yourself off the ground. The tool you are using IS the trap. So what works? Prapadyante — surrender. Not intellectual surrender where you read three books on Vedanta and say 'I get it.' REAL surrender. The kind where you stop pretending you have it all figured out. Where you admit that your five-year plan, your carefully curated identity, your confident LinkedIn bio — all of it is a house of cards. And you just... let go. Into something bigger than your mind can hold. THOSE people, Krishna says, cross over. Not by fighting maya. By falling into the arms of the One who CREATED maya."
