          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just dropped the most SAVAGE classification of non-devotees in the history of spiritual literature. Four types of people who will NEVER surrender, and honestly, you probably know all four. First — MŪḌHĀḤ, the foolish. These are not unintelligent people. These are people who are smart about EVERYTHING except the one thing that matters. They can calculate compound interest, optimize their stock portfolio, crack CAT exams — but ask them 'Who am I?' and they stare at you like you asked them to solve a math problem in Sanskrit. The fool is not the one who does not KNOW — the fool is the one who does not even know what is WORTH knowing. Second — NARĀDHAMĀḤ, the lowest of mankind. Now this is not about caste or birth. This is about someone who HAD the human capacity for awakening and WASTED it. You got the rarest gift in creation — a human mind capable of self-realization — and you used it exclusively to fight on Twitter, hoard wealth, and destroy others. That is like getting a Stradivarius violin and using it to scratch your back. Third — MĀYAYĀPAHṚTA-JÑĀNĀḤ, those whose knowledge has been stolen by maya. THIS is the scariest category because these people LOOK wise. They have read the books, they attend satsangs, they can quote scriptures. But their actual OPERATING SYSTEM is still running on ego, desire, and fear. These are the spiritual influencers with 500K followers who are secretly checking their engagement metrics during meditation. They HAVE knowledge, but maya STOLE the essence and left them with the packaging. Fourth — ĀSURA BHĀVAM, those of demonic nature. These actively work AGAINST dharma. Not out of ignorance but out of choice. They see goodness and want to destroy it. They see truth and want to suppress it. Every scammer who cheats elderly people of their savings, every troll who spreads hatred for fun, every person who deliberately corrupts what is sacred — āsura bhāvam. Notice: Krishna does not say these people CANNOT surrender. He says they DO NOT. The door is never locked. They just refuse to walk through it."
