          modernInterpretation: "This is Krishna explaining why most people walk right past God without recognizing Him — and the answer is YOGA-MAYA, his own divine cloaking device. Think of it as the ultimate VPN. God is browsing this universe in incognito mode, and most people cannot see his real identity. Krishna says: I am not hidden because I am absent. I am hidden because I am VEILED. There is a massive difference. The sun during a solar eclipse is not gone — it is covered. And the covering here is yoga-maya, which is not some evil trick. It is Krishna's own creative power. He CHOOSES not to be obvious. Why? Because if God walked around with a neon sign saying 'I AM GOD,' free will would collapse. Nobody would sin. Nobody would struggle. Nobody would GROW. The exam would be pointless if the teacher stood at the front holding up the answer sheet. So Krishna plays the most incredible game in existence — He hides in plain sight. He is in the chai you drink, the sunrise you ignore, the stranger who helps you, the silence between your thoughts. But the world is MUDHA — deluded. We are so busy scrolling through reels, refreshing LinkedIn, checking Swiggy delivery status, that we cannot see the divine operating system running behind everything. It is like fish asking 'where is the water?' You are swimming in it, bro. This verse also explains why spiritual masters are often unrecognized in their time. Jesus was a carpenter's son. Buddha was a dropout prince. Kabir was a weaver. The packaging never matches the product when it comes to the divine. If you are waiting for God to show up with special effects and background music, you will be waiting forever. He already showed up. You just did not notice."
