          modernInterpretation: "Krishna is now talking about the SERIOUS seekers. Not the casual spiritual tourists who read one self-help book and post quotes on Instagram. He is talking about people who have looked at the human condition — JARA and MARANA, old age and death — and said: 'I refuse to accept this as the final answer.' These are people who have seen their grandparents age. Seen their parents slow down. Noticed their own first grey hair, first back pain, first moment of 'I cannot do what I used to.' And instead of just buying anti-aging cream and pretending it is not happening, they ask the REAL question: is there something beyond this cycle? Is there liberation from this biological countdown timer? And Krishna says: those who come to ME with this question — not to a Google search, not to a YouTube guru, not to their WhatsApp group — but to the SOURCE itself — they end up knowing EVERYTHING. Brahma — the ultimate reality. Adhyatma — the nature of the self. Karma — how action truly works in its entirety. It is like going to a university to study one subject and accidentally getting a PhD in everything. Because when you seek the fundamental truth, all other truths are included. When you understand the ocean, you automatically understand waves, tides, currents, and every fish in it. Most people try to understand life piecemeal — a little psychology here, a little philosophy there, some astrology, some motivational podcasts. But Krishna says: take refuge in ME, and the entire syllabus becomes clear. Not in parts. KRITSNAM — completely. AKHILAM — in its entirety. This verse is the ultimate elevator pitch for surrendering to the divine: 'Come to me with your deepest fear, and I will give you the deepest knowledge.'"
