          translation: "And whoever, at the time of death, remembers Me alone and departs, leaving the body — that one attains My being. There is no doubt about this.",
          modernInterpretation: "This is THE verse. The one that changes everything. Krishna says: your LAST THOUGHT decides your NEXT DESTINATION. Not your caste, not your bank balance, not how many temples you visited, not your LinkedIn endorsements. Your LAST THOUGHT. 'Nāsty atra saṁśayaḥ' — there is NO DOUBT about this. Krishna uses this phrase like a legal stamp. This is not a suggestion, not a possibility — this is a GUARANTEE. Think of death like the final exam of life. It does not matter how many classes you attended or how many notes you borrowed. What matters is what you WRITE in those three hours. And your last thought is your final answer sheet. But here is the catch that most people miss: you cannot suddenly think of God at death if you have spent your whole life thinking about EMIs, promotions, and what your neighbour's kid scored in JEE. The last thought is not a random event — it is the RESULT of a lifetime of practice. Your mind at death will go where it has been TRAINED to go. If it has been trained on Instagram Reels, it will go to Instagram Reels. If it has been trained on the Divine — it goes to the Divine. Simple as that. No cheat codes. No last-minute jugaad."
