          translation: "Therefore, at all times remember Me and fight. With mind and intellect surrendered to Me, you shall surely come to Me alone — there is no doubt.",
          modernInterpretation: "THIS is the practical instruction everyone has been waiting for. And notice — Krishna does NOT say 'Quit your job, go to the Himalayas, and meditate.' He says TWO things: REMEMBER ME. And FIGHT. Both. Simultaneously. Not one or the other. This is Krishna's genius. He is not asking Arjuna to become a monk. He is asking him to become a WARRIOR-MONK. Do your duty — write your code, teach your students, drive your Ola, prepare your UPSC — but do it while REMEMBERING the Divine. This is the original multitasking advice, and it is FAR more practical than anything any productivity guru will sell you on Instagram. 'Mām anusmara yudhya ca' — remember Me AND fight. The 'and' is everything. Spirituality is not an escape FROM life. It is a way of being IN life. The rickshaw driver who remembers God while navigating Bangalore traffic is more spiritual than the guru who meditates in an air-conditioned ashram but loses his temper when his chai is late. 'Arpita-mano-buddhiḥ' — mind AND intellect offered to God. Not just emotion, not just logic — BOTH. Your heart AND your brain, aligned in one direction. When that happens, Krishna says, 'asaṁśayam' — WITHOUT DOUBT — you reach Me. No maybe. No probably. GUARANTEED."
