          modernInterpretation: "Krishna is about to drop the MOST concise product pitch in all of spiritual literature. He says: 'There is this thing — the Vedic scholars talk about it, the monks chase it, people give up relationships and Netflix subscriptions for it — and I am going to explain it to you in SHORT.' SANGRAHEN. In brief. Think about that. The ultimate reality, the thing that every Upanishad spends hundreds of pages on, every guru builds an entire ashram around — Krishna says 'Let me give you the Twitter version.' Now look at the three categories of people who seek this AKSHARA — the imperishable. First, the VEDA-VIDAH — the scholars, the people who have studied all the texts, cracked the spiritual equivalent of UPSC. They know it intellectually. Second, the YATAYAH VITA-RAGAH — the ascetics who have given up passion. These are not armchair philosophers. These are people who have actually walked away from comfort. No Zomato Pro. No Amazon Prime. No Instagram reels at 2 AM. They have DONE the work. Third, those who practice BRAHMACHARYA — not just celibacy, but complete self-discipline. Channeling every ounce of energy toward the divine. And all three groups — the scholars, the monks, and the disciplined seekers — are going after the SAME thing. Different routes, same destination. Like how Ola, Metro, and auto-rickshaws all eventually get you to Koramangala. Krishna says: I will tell you what that destination IS. And I will keep it brief. Because the deepest truths do not need long explanations. They need READINESS."
