          modernInterpretation: "This verse is a REALITY CHECK for spiritual overachievers. You think reaching heaven is the endgame? You think if you do enough puja, collect enough karma points, maybe get upgraded to Brahmaloka — the HIGHEST realm in creation, the VIP lounge of the cosmos — you are set forever? WRONG. PUNAR AVARTINAḤ. Subject to return. Even Brahmaloka has a checkout time. Even the penthouse suite of the universe comes with an expiry date. This is like finding out that even your lifetime Amazon Prime membership has terms and conditions. Even if you make it to Brahma's realm — and that is like being the CEO of the entire cosmic corporation — your contract STILL ends eventually, and you get sent back into the cycle. Think about how humbling that is. The HIGHEST created being, Brahma himself, lives in a temporary realm. His world dissolves. His inhabitants return to the cycle. If even the cosmic CEO does not have permanent tenure, what chance does your corner-office karma have? But then Krishna drops the contrast: MAM UPETYA TU — but having reached ME. That one word TU — 'but' — changes everything. It is the most powerful 'but' in all of scripture. Every realm is temporary BUT Mine. Every achievement fades BUT this one. Every destination has a return ticket BUT this one. PUNAR JANMA NA VIDYATE — rebirth simply does not exist for those who reach Krishna. Not 'rebirth is delayed.' Not 'rebirth is reduced.' It does NOT EXIST. Krishna is not offering you a better room in the hotel of samsara. He is offering you a HOME. The difference between every other spiritual achievement and reaching Krishna is the difference between a hotel stay and owning a house. One ends. The other is yours forever."
