          modernInterpretation: "Krishna is describing the COSMIC BREATHING of the universe. When Brahma's day begins — AHAR AGAME — everything MANIFESTS. Galaxies, stars, planets, life, consciousness, beings — all of it emerges from the AVYAKTA, the unmanifest. Like the ultimate startup launch day. Everything that was in stealth mode suddenly goes live. And when Brahma's night comes — RATRI AGAME — everything DISSOLVES back. Not destroyed — dissolved. PRALEEYANTE. It merges back into the unmanifest source from which it came. Like closing all the tabs at the end of the day. Every browser window, every app, every document — gone. But the computer is still there. The hard drive still holds everything. Nothing is truly lost — it is just not DISPLAYED anymore. This is the original cloud computing. The universe stores everything in the AVYAKTA — the unmanifest cloud — and deploys it fresh every cosmic morning. Your entire existence, everything you have ever known, every star you have ever seen in the night sky — it is all a DAY SHIFT project that gets shelved when the cosmic clock strikes evening. And the most humbling part? This has been happening since beginningless time. We think our universe is special, our Big Bang is unique. But Krishna is telling us this has happened THOUSANDS of times before. Manifest. Dissolve. Manifest. Dissolve. Like the breath of some impossibly vast being — inhale, the universe appears. Exhale, it disappears. And we — with our five-year plans and ten-year goals — are making plans inside a single breath."
