          modernInterpretation: "Krishna is basically saying there is a destination from which NO ONE books a return ticket. Think about it — every other achievement in life has a 'return policy.' You crack IIT, you still come back to job hunting. You get a US visa, you still come back for mom's dal. You reach the top of your startup valuation, the market crashes and you are back to zero. EVERYTHING in this material world is a ROUND TRIP. But Krishna says there is ONE destination — His supreme abode — where the journey is ONE WAY. No return. No rebirth. No more Monday mornings. No more Bangalore traffic. No more 'let us circle back on this.' This AKSARA, this imperishable reality, is not some place in the sky with golden gates. It is the state of consciousness where you realize you were NEVER separate from the Divine in the first place. It is like finally understanding that the Wi-Fi signal was strong all along — you just had airplane mode on. The moment you switch it off, you are CONNECTED forever. No buffering. No disconnection. That is the PARAMAM DHAMA — the ultimate home. And once you are home, why would you leave?"
