          modernInterpretation: "THIS IS THE CRESCENDO. Verses 16, 17, and 18 form a TRINITY OF TOTALITY, and this verse is the peak. Listen to these words — each one is a UNIVERSE of meaning. GATI — I am the goal. Every dream you chase, every destination you type into Google Maps, every 'where do I see myself in 5 years' answer — it all leads to ME. BHARTA — I am the sustainer. Your salary is not sustaining you. Your health insurance is not sustaining you. I AM. PRABHU — I am the master. Not the toxic boss kind. The kind who OWNS the whole game but still lets you play freely. SAKSHI — I am the witness. When nobody sees your struggle, your 2 AM tears, your silent sacrifices — I SEE. I am the CCTV of the cosmos, but with compassion. NIVASA — I am the abode. You think home is your 2BHK in Bangalore? Home is ME. SHARANAM — I am the shelter. When the world falls apart, when the startup fails, when the relationship ends — I am the umbrella in the storm. SUHRIT — I am the FRIEND. Not the friend who only shows up for the good times. The friend who has NO SELFISH MOTIVE. The truest, most selfless friend you will ever have. PRABHAVA and PRALAYA — I am both the Big Bang AND the Big Crunch. The birth and the death. The login and the logout. STHANAM — I am the foundation. NIDHANAM — I am where everything rests. BIJAM AVYAYAM — I am the IMPERISHABLE SEED. Every tree, every life, every galaxy — they all sprouted from this one indestructible seed. This verse is not theology. It is a LOVE LETTER from the universe to you."
