          modernInterpretation: "After the cosmic LinkedIn profile of verses 16-18, Krishna gets PRACTICAL. 'I control the weather.' That scorching May heat in Delhi that makes you question all your life choices? That is Me. The first monsoon rain that makes Mumbai simultaneously flood and rejoice? Also Me. I WITHHOLD the rain — hello, drought, water crisis, tanker mafia. And I RELEASE it — hello, floods, Bangalore traffic underwater, 'work from home due to waterlogging.' Then He goes DEEP: 'I am amritam AND mrityu.' Immortality AND death. Life AND its ending. Not one or the other — BOTH. This is the part most people struggle with. We want a God who is only good things — sunshine, promotions, and perfectly timed Swiggy deliveries. But Krishna says: 'I am also the darkness, the loss, the ending.' SAT and ASAT — existence and non-existence. The things that ARE and the things that ARE NOT. The presence and the absence. Your greatest joy and your deepest grief — same source. This is not cruelty. This is COMPLETENESS. A God who is only the good stuff is not God. He is a vending machine."
