          modernInterpretation: "HERE IS THE RUG PULL. Remember those celestial tourists from the last verse? The ones living it up in Indra's penthouse? KSHINE PUNYE — when the merit runs out, when the prepaid balance hits zero, when the subscription expires — MARTYA LOKAM VISHANTI — they CRASH LAND back into the mortal world. Imagine: you saved up for years, went on the most incredible Maldives vacation, posted 47 stories, got 500 likes, and then... Monday morning. Bangalore traffic. Cold office AC. Passive-aggressive emails. That is what happens to these heaven-goers. Except instead of Monday blues, it is an ENTIRE NEW BIRTH in the mortal world. GATAGATAM — coming and going, coming and going. The cosmic revolving door. Up to heaven, back to earth. Up again, back again. Like a spiritual yo-yo. KAMA-KAMA — desiring desires. Not even satisfied with what they get — they keep wanting MORE. This is the Amazon Prime trap applied to the soul. You get what you ordered, but by the time it arrives, you want something else. Krishna's message is devastatingly simple: if you worship the INFINITE for FINITE rewards, you get finite results. Period. The tragedy is not that they suffer. The tragedy is that they had access to EVERYTHING and settled for temporary upgrades."
