          translation: "Those who worship Me alone, thinking of no other, to those ever-united devotees, I carry what they lack and preserve what they have.",
          modernInterpretation: "Stop everything. Read this verse again. And again. This is arguably the MOST POWERFUL PROMISE ever made in the history of spiritual literature. Let it sink in: YOGA-KSHEMAM VAHAMY AHAM — 'I PERSONALLY CARRY what you lack and protect what you have.' Not 'I will arrange for it.' Not 'I will send someone.' Not 'I will put it in the pipeline and circle back.' VAHAMI — I CARRY it. MYSELF. On MY shoulders. Like a mother carrying groceries home for her children. Like a father carrying his sleeping child from the car to the bed. PERSONALLY.\n\nYoga means acquisition — the things you do not yet have. Kshema means preservation — the things you already have. Krishna says: 'BOTH are on Me.' Your future AND your present. Your growth AND your security. Your dreams AND your current reality. I HANDLE IT ALL.\n\nBut there is a condition. And it is the hardest condition in the world: ANANYAH — thinking of NO OTHER. Not 'primarily Me with a few backups.' Not 'Me on Sundays and your own cleverness on weekdays.' ONLY ME. EXCLUSIVELY. This is the spiritual equivalent of going all-in. No hedge funds, no diversified portfolio, no Plan B. Just TOTAL SURRENDER.\n\nNITYABHIYUKTANAM — ever steadfast. Not people who remember God only during board exams, medical emergencies, and flight turbulence. People who are ALWAYS connected. In joy and sorrow, in profit and loss, in Zomato delivering on time AND Zomato showing 'delayed.'\n\nThere is a famous story: when Sri Ramanujacharya was teaching this verse, he wept. His students asked why. He said, 'Because the Lord of the universe — the one who commands galaxies and controls time itself — has REDUCED HIMSELF to a delivery boy for His devotees. He said VAHAMI — I carry. The Supreme Being, carrying your yoga-kshema like a Swiggy rider with your order on his back.'\n\nThis is not transactional religion. This is not 'I will give you something if you give Me something.' This is a BLANK CHECK signed by the creator of the universe. The only endorsement required? YOUR COMPLETE TRUST.\n\nEvery insurance company promises security. Every investment app promises growth. Every self-help guru promises both. But they all come with terms and conditions, hidden charges, and exit loads. Krishna's promise has ONE condition: love Me completely. That is it. No KYC, no documentation, no processing fee. Just ANANYA BHAKTI — undivided devotion.\n\nThis verse was reportedly so precious to the Alvars and Acharyas that they considered it the ESSENCE of the entire Gita. Forget 700 verses — if you TRULY understood this one verse and LIVED it, you would need nothing else. The God who built the cosmos promises to personally deliver your groceries. If that does not move you, check your pulse."
