          modernInterpretation: "If verse 26 told you WHAT to offer, verse 27 tells you HOW to live. And the answer is breathtaking in its simplicity — EVERYTHING is worship. You are eating lunch? That is worship. You are writing code at 2 AM in Bangalore? That is worship. You are stuck in Mumbai local train? WORSHIP. You are changing your baby's diaper at 4 AM? That is the highest puja. Krishna is not asking you to BECOME a monk. He is asking you to turn your EXISTING life into a temple. 'Mad-arpanam' — as an offering to Me. This is the Gita's answer to the modern work-life-spirituality balance problem. You do not need to quit your job and go to the Himalayas. You do not need to wake up at 4 AM for meditation if you are already sleep-deprived. You do not need a special room, special clothes, or a special time. Just add three words to everything you do: 'FOR YOU, KRISHNA.' Making Maggi at midnight? For You. Sending that difficult email to the client? For You. Sitting through a boring meeting? For You. Paying EMIs? For You. This one mental shift transforms the MUNDANE into the SACRED. Your office becomes a temple. Your work becomes puja. Your salary becomes prasad. You are already doing everything — Krishna is just asking you to change the DEDICATION. Same actions, divine purpose."
