          modernInterpretation: "This is the PAYOFF for verse 27. You offered everything to Krishna? Great — now here is what happens: you are FREE. Free from what? From the endless cycle of 'good karma, bad karma.' See, most people think karma is like a report card — good marks, bad marks. But Krishna is saying BOTH are chains. Getting a promotion is a golden chain. Getting fired is an iron chain. But BOTH are chains. The only way to break free is to stop collecting karma altogether — and you do that by offering every action to the Divine. It is like playing a video game but handing the controller to God. The game still plays, you still act, but the SCORE does not stick to you. You become like a non-stick pan — life happens ON you but nothing STICKS. 'Sannyasa-yoga-yuktatma' — this is not about wearing saffron and leaving home. This is about INNER renunciation. You can be a CEO, a mother, a student, a Swiggy delivery partner — and still be a sannyasi INSIDE. How? By doing everything for Krishna. Not for the result. Not for the applause. Not for the Instagram post. FOR KRISHNA. And when nothing sticks — no pride, no regret, no attachment, no fear — that is MOKSHA. That is liberation. Not after death. RIGHT NOW. You come to Krishna not in some distant afterlife — you come to Him in THIS moment, the moment you let go."
