          modernInterpretation: "Read this verse and WEEP. This is the most RADICAL statement of grace in all of spiritual literature. Krishna is saying: 'Even the WORST person — the one society has written off, the one the courts have convicted, the one whose own family has given up on him — if that person turns to Me with GENUINE, EXCLUSIVE devotion, call him a SAINT.' Not 'he will become a saint eventually.' Not 'he is on the path to sainthood.' SADHU EVA — he IS a saint. RIGHT NOW. In that very moment of turning. This is not about excusing sin. This is about the POWER of genuine transformation. Think about it — we live in a world that DEFINES people by their worst moments. One mistake on social media and your career is over. One bad decision and you are cancelled forever. Society stamps 'REJECTED' on people and throws away the key. But Krishna? Krishna says: 'I do not care about your PAST. I care about your PRESENT devotion.' This is not cheap forgiveness. Notice the condition — 'ananya-bhak' — EXCLUSIVE devotion. Not casual. Not part-time. Not 'I will worship when things go bad and forget when things are good.' TOTAL, absolute, all-consuming devotion. When a person makes that shift — when they turn from darkness to light with their ENTIRE being — the past burns away like camphor. It does not matter how far you have fallen. What matters is which direction you are NOW facing. The prodigal son does not need a resume update. He just needs to come HOME."
