          modernInterpretation: "Verse 30 was the promise. Verse 31 is the GUARANTEE. And notice something extraordinary — Krishna does not say 'I declare.' He tells ARJUNA: 'YOU declare it. Pratijanihi — YOU announce it to the world.' Why? Because when God makes a promise, people say 'that is scripture.' But when a HUMAN declares it — a struggling, confused, imperfect human like Arjuna — it becomes TESTIMONY. It becomes relatable. Krishna is saying: 'Arjuna, stand up and tell everyone — MY DEVOTEE NEVER PERISHES. Put your name on this guarantee.' This is God asking a human to be His brand ambassador. Not because God needs marketing — but because HUMANS need to hear it from another human. 'Kshipram bhavati dharmatma' — QUICKLY he becomes righteous. Not in seven lifetimes. Not after decades of penance. QUICKLY. Because devotion is not a slow renovation — it is a controlled demolition followed by instant reconstruction. The old building of sin comes crashing down, and in its place rises a temple. And then — 'shashvat shantim' — ETERNAL peace. Not temporary calm. Not 'I feel better after meditation' peace. LASTING, UNSHAKEABLE peace. The kind of peace that remains when the stock market crashes, when the diagnosis is bad, when the relationship ends. The kind of peace that does not depend on circumstances. 'Na me bhaktah pranashyati' — My devotee NEVER perishes. Never. Not 'rarely.' Not 'usually.' NEVER. This is Krishna's ABSOLUTE guarantee. Write it on your wall. Save it as your phone wallpaper. Tattoo it on your soul. His devotee. Never. Perishes."
