          modernInterpretation: "Welcome to Chapter 10, folks. VIBHUTI YOGA. The chapter where Krishna basically opens His cosmic LinkedIn profile and says 'Let me tell you about My endorsements.' But first — notice the tone. He says 'prīyamāṇāya' — to one who is BELOVED. This is not a lecture. This is not a boss giving a performance review. This is someone who LOVES you, pulling you aside and saying, 'Listen, I am going to tell you something important because I genuinely care about you.'\n\nThink about it — in your life, how many people give you advice because they actually want your good? Your parents sometimes. A real mentor, maybe. Most advice comes with an agenda — 'Do this course' (because I get a referral bonus), 'Join this startup' (because I need co-founders), 'Invest in this' (because I am already invested). But Krishna says 'hita-kāmyayā' — I am telling you this PURELY because I want your welfare. No commission. No affiliate link. No 'use my code KRISHNA10 for 10% off.'\n\nAlso notice — He says 'AGAIN.' He has already explained everything in chapters 7-9. But He is going AGAIN. Because REAL teaching is repetition. Your gym trainer does not tell you once and walk away. Your Carnatic music teacher makes you sing the same varnam 400 times. Krishna is the ultimate guru — He does not get frustrated that you did not get it the first time. He just says 'Cool, let me explain again, differently, with MORE detail.' This is the energy we need from every teacher, every parent, every manager. Not 'I already told you once.' But 'Let me tell you AGAIN, because you matter to me.' That is love. That is divine teaching. Chapter 10 starts HERE."
