          translation: "Neither the hosts of devas nor the great sages know My origin, for I am the source of the devas and the great sages in every way.",
          modernInterpretation: "This is the ultimate flex — but also the most humbling truth. Krishna says even the DEVAS — Indra, Brahma, the cosmic CEOs running the universe — do not fully know Him. Even the greatest RISHIS — Vasishtha, Vishwamitra, beings who have meditated for thousands of years — cannot fully comprehend His origin.\n\nWhy? Because YOU CANNOT KNOW WHAT CREATED YOU. The painting cannot fully understand the painter. The code cannot fully debug the programmer. Your iPhone does not know who Tim Cook is. The CREATION can never fully wrap its head around the CREATOR because the creator is always bigger than anything the creation can imagine.\n\nThis is why every time science discovers something, there is something deeper behind it. Atoms? Surprise — there are subatomic particles. Subatomic particles? Surprise — there is quantum foam. It is turtles all the way down. And Krishna is saying, 'I am the turtle at the VERY bottom — and even that is not the full picture.' No amount of IIT-level intellect, no UPSC topper's analytical brain, no PhD from MIT can fully grasp the ORIGIN of origins. Not because we are stupid, but because the INFINITE cannot be contained by the finite. And accepting that is actually the BEGINNING of wisdom."
