          transliteration: "maharṣayaḥ sapta pūrve catvāro manavas tathā |\nmad-bhāvā mānasā jātā yeṣāṁ loka imāḥ prajāḥ ||6||",
          words: [
            { word: "महर्षयः", transliteration: "maharṣayaḥ", meaning: "the great sages" },
            { word: "सप्त", transliteration: "sapta", meaning: "seven" },
            { word: "पूर्वे", transliteration: "pūrve", meaning: "ancient" },
            { word: "चत्वारः", transliteration: "catvāraḥ", meaning: "four" },
            { word: "मनवः", transliteration: "manavaḥ", meaning: "Manus" },
            { word: "तथा", transliteration: "tathā", meaning: "also" },
            { word: "मद्भावाः", transliteration: "mad-bhāvāḥ", meaning: "born of My nature" },
            { word: "मानसाः", transliteration: "mānasāḥ", meaning: "from the mind" },
            { word: "जाताः", transliteration: "jātāḥ", meaning: "born" },
            { word: "येषाम्", transliteration: "yeṣām", meaning: "of whom" },
            { word: "लोके", transliteration: "loke", meaning: "in the world" },
            { word: "इमाः", transliteration: "imāḥ", meaning: "these" },
            { word: "प्रजाः", transliteration: "prajāḥ", meaning: "beings/creatures" }
          ],
          translation: "The seven great sages, the four ancient Manus, and all beings in the world are born from My mind.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just casually drops that the seven Maharishis — Marichi, Atri, Angiras, Pulastya, Pulaha, Kratu, Vasishtha — and the four Manus (the progenitors of humanity) were all BORN FROM HIS MIND. Not from a factory. Not from a lab. From His THOUGHT. He literally THOUGHT them into existence.\n\nImagine if your THOUGHTS could create entire civilizations. You think about pizza and an entire pizza ecosystem comes into existence — farmers, chefs, Zomato delivery guys, the whole thing. That is what Krishna does, except with COSMIC BEINGS who then create everything else. He is the founder who created the founding team who built the company called 'Universe.'\n\nThe word 'mānasā' — from the mind — is key. It means creation is fundamentally a MENTAL act, not a physical one. The universe is not manufactured — it is IMAGINED. And every creature in every world traces back to that one cosmic imagination. You, me, your neighbor's annoying dog, the auto driver who takes the long route — all of us are thoughts in the mind of the Divine. Let that humble you next time you think you are self-made."
