          transliteration: "teṣāṁ satata-yuktānāṁ bhajatāṁ prīti-pūrvakam |\ndadāmi buddhi-yogaṁ taṁ yena mām upayānti te ||10||",
          words: [
            { word: "तेषाम्", transliteration: "teṣām", meaning: "to them" },
            { word: "सततयुक्तानाम्", transliteration: "satata-yuktānām", meaning: "constantly united" },
            { word: "भजताम्", transliteration: "bhajatām", meaning: "who worship" },
            { word: "प्रीतिपूर्वकम्", transliteration: "prīti-pūrvakam", meaning: "with love" },
            { word: "ददामि", transliteration: "dadāmi", meaning: "I give" },
            { word: "बुद्धियोगम्", transliteration: "buddhi-yogam", meaning: "yoga of understanding" },
            { word: "तम्", transliteration: "tam", meaning: "that" },
            { word: "येन", transliteration: "yena", meaning: "by which" },
            { word: "माम्", transliteration: "mām", meaning: "Me" },
            { word: "उपयान्ति", transliteration: "upayānti", meaning: "come to" },
            { word: "ते", transliteration: "te", meaning: "they" }
          ],
          translation: "To those who are constantly united and who worship Me with love, I give the yoga of understanding (buddhi-yoga) by which they come to Me.",
          modernInterpretation: "This is the most PERSONAL promise Krishna makes. He says — you do YOUR part (love Me, stay connected), and I will PERSONALLY give you the intelligence to reach Me. 'Dadāmi' — I GIVE. First person. Not 'it will happen' or 'the universe will provide.' I, KRISHNA, PERSONALLY, will give you buddhi-yoga — the CLARITY of understanding that leads you HOME.\n\nTwo conditions: 'satata-yuktānām' — CONSTANTLY connected, not just when you are in trouble. And 'prīti-pūrvakam' — with LOVE, not with fear or greed. If you come to God only during board exams and job interviews, this deal does not apply. If you pray only because you are scared of hell, this deal does not apply. But if you genuinely, consistently, lovingly stay connected — He PERSONALLY upgrades your spiritual GPS.\n\nThis is like having a direct line to the CEO. Not through HR, not through a chatbot, not through a support ticket. DIRECT. And what does He give? Not money, not fame, not a better Instagram following. He gives BUDDHI — the understanding that dissolves all confusion. Because once you have THAT, you do not need anything else. You find your way HOME."
