          modernInterpretation: "Arjuna FINALLY gets it. After nine chapters of questions, doubts, confusion, and cosmic revelations, something has CLICKED. And when he speaks, he does not say 'I think You might be God.' He says it with FULL CONVICTION — param brahma, param dhāma, pavitram paramam. Supreme Brahman. Supreme Abode. Supreme Purifier. No hedging. No 'maybe.' No 'in my humble opinion.'\n\nThis is the moment in every spiritual journey when intellectual understanding becomes LIVED EXPERIENCE. It is like the difference between reading about Bangalore weather and actually standing in the rain on MG Road. Theory became reality. And once that shift happens, there is no going back.\n\nNotice the words Arjuna uses — ādi-devam (PRIMAL God, the first of all gods), ajam (UNBORN — never created), vibhum (ALL-PERVADING — everywhere at once). This is not casual praise. This is Arjuna deploying the most precise theological vocabulary available. He is not just impressed — he is TRANSFORMED. The warrior who was crying in Chapter 1 is now speaking like a philosopher-saint in Chapter 10. THAT is what proximity to truth does to you."
