          modernInterpretation: "This is Arjuna's declaration of TOTAL FAITH. 'Sarvam etad ṛtaṁ manye' — I accept ALL of this as TRUE. Not 'most of it.' Not 'the parts that are convenient.' ALL of it. This is the moment the student fully SURRENDERS to the teaching. And there is something beautiful about the word 'ṛtam' — it does not just mean 'true' in a factual sense. It means TRUE in a cosmic sense — aligned with the fundamental order of reality.\n\nAnd then Arjuna adds the humbling coda — even the DEVAS (gods) and DANAVAS (demons) do not fully know Your manifestation. Think about that. The most powerful beings in existence, whether good or evil, whether divine or demonic — NONE of them can fully comprehend Krishna. Not because they are not smart enough, but because the INFINITE cannot be boxed by the finite.\n\nThis is Arjuna saying, 'I may not understand everything, but I TRUST everything You say.' And that trust is not weakness — it is the highest form of intelligence. Because sometimes the smartest thing you can do is admit that some things are beyond your comprehension and trust the one who DOES comprehend. Like a patient trusting a surgeon. You do not need to understand every step of the operation. You need to trust the hands that hold the scalpel. Arjuna trusts the hands that hold the universe."
