          modernInterpretation: "This is one of the most PHILOSOPHICALLY dense verses in the entire Gita. Think about it. The letter A. In Sanskrit, EVERY letter begins with A. You cannot say ka without the a — it is ka, not k. You cannot say ma without the a — it is ma, not m. The letter A is the FOUNDATION upon which the entire language, all communication, all knowledge rests. Krishna is saying: I am the PREREQUISITE of all expression. Before you can say ANYTHING — any word, any thought, any prayer — I am already there. I am the canvas before the painting. The silence before the song. The blank page before the code. Among compound words, He is dvandva — the compound of EQUALS. Ram-Lakshman. Sita-Ram. Day-night. Joy-sorrow. The Divine holds OPPOSITES together without contradiction. And then the deepest line: 'I am INEXHAUSTIBLE time.' Not time that runs out. Not your deadline. Not your countdown timer. AKSHAYA kala — time that never depletes, never exhausts, never ends. Your clock ticks. God's clock does not even HAVE hands. He is the creator facing EVERYWHERE — vishvatomukha — seeing all directions simultaneously. No blind spots. No back camera needed. No rear-view mirror. The Divine is watching the past, present, and future in a single glance. Your CCTV cameras cover four angles. God covers infinity."
