          modernInterpretation: "Danda — the rod. Not anger. Not revenge. STRUCTURED punishment. The law. The system. Without danda, there is no civilization — just chaos with better outfits. Every traffic challan, every court ruling, every parent's stern 'NO' that saves a child from disaster — that is danda. That is the Divine maintaining ORDER in a world that naturally tends toward chaos. Of those who seek victory — NITI. Not brute force. Not aggression. STATESMANSHIP. Strategy. Chanakya-level thinking. The victory that comes not from fighting harder but from thinking SMARTER. Every successful negotiation, every deal closed without a fight, every war avoided through diplomacy — that is Krishna. And then the REAL gem: of secrets, I am SILENCE. Let that land. The best-kept secret in the universe is not a password or a classified document. It is SILENCE itself. Because the deepest truths cannot be spoken — they can only be experienced in stillness. Your meditation practice, those rare moments at 4 AM when the world is quiet and something inside you just KNOWS — that knowing IS God. Every WhatsApp forward is noise. Every tweet is noise. Every opinion is noise. But that silence where wisdom lives? THAT is sacred. And of the wise — He is not their degrees or their publications. He is their JNANA — the knowing itself. Not information. Not data. WISDOM. The difference between knowing the path and walking it."
