          modernInterpretation: "This is the SEED verse. Literally. Krishna says: whatever is the BIJA — the seed, the DNA, the source code — of every living thing, that is Me. Before the banyan tree was a tree, it was a seed. Before you were you, you were a possibility. That POSSIBILITY — the potential, the latent energy, the spark that says 'this will become SOMETHING' — that is God. Nothing exists without Him. NOTHING. Not the ant on your kitchen counter. Not the bacteria in your gut. Not the cockroach you are terrified of. Not the stray dog you fed yesterday. Not the tree you ignore on your morning walk. Every single thing that moves — characharam — and everything that does not move — the mountain, the rock, the ground beneath your feet — ALL of it is sustained by the Divine. Pull God out, and the whole thing collapses like a Jenga tower on the last move. This verse destroys the illusion that spirituality is about temples and rituals. If NOTHING can exist without God, then your office is a temple. Your kitchen is a temple. The Bangalore traffic jam at 6 PM is a temple — a very noisy, frustrating temple, but a temple nonetheless. You cannot escape the Divine. You can only stop NOTICING it."
