          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just spent 40 verses listing the greatest manifestations in the universe — the best of every category, the pinnacle of every domain — and now He casually says: 'Oh, by the way, that was just the TRAILER. The movie is infinitely longer.' Imagine watching a three-hour Netflix documentary about the universe and then being told: 'That was 0.0001% of the content.' The entire Vibhuti Yoga chapter — all these glories, from Vishnu to Shiva, from the Ganges to the Himalayas, from the letter A to time itself — was just an UDDESHA. A brief indication. A WhatsApp summary of an infinite library. Krishna is saying: 'Arjuna, your HUMAN MIND cannot contain My full glory. I gave you highlights because your brain would crash if I gave you the full file. You are running a 64-bit processor and My glory requires INFINITE bits.' This is divine humility wrapped in divine power. He does not say this to boast. He says it so Arjuna understands that no matter how much you KNOW about God, there is always infinitely more to discover. The spiritual journey never ends. Every realization opens a thousand new doors. Every answer births a thousand new questions. And THAT is the beauty of it."
