          translation: "Whatever being is glorious, prosperous, or powerful — know that to be a manifestation of a fraction of My splendor.",
          modernInterpretation: "Read that word again: AMSHA. A fraction. A FRACTION. Everything glorious you have ever witnessed — every breathtaking sunset over the Arabian Sea, every Sachin Tendulkar straight drive, every A.R. Rahman composition that made you cry, every SpaceX rocket landing, every mother holding her newborn, every act of kindness that restored your faith in humanity — ALL of that is a fraction. A SPARK. A single pixel in an infinite screen. The Himalayas that take your breath away? Fraction. The ocean that makes you feel small? Fraction. The love that makes you feel infinite? Still a fraction. That genius coder who built an app that changed millions of lives? A fraction of divine tejas working through human hands. That teacher in a government school who inspired generations? A fraction. That farmer who feeds nations without ever trending on Twitter? A fraction. Virat Kohli's cover drive, the northern lights, a baby's first laugh, the smell of rain on dry earth — all FRACTIONS. Now sit with this: if the FRACTION is this magnificent, this awe-inspiring, this overwhelmingly beautiful — what must the WHOLE look like? What must the SOURCE be? That question — that impossible, mind-breaking, heart-expanding question — is exactly where Krishna wants Arjuna's mind to go. And it is exactly where your mind should go right now."
