          modernInterpretation: "Welcome to Chapter 11 — VISHVARUPA DARSHANA YOGA — The Yoga of the Universal Form. This is the MARVEL ENDGAME of the Bhagavad Gita. The Infinity War is OVER. Now we see what the Infinity Stones actually look like when ONE being holds ALL of reality.\n\nArjuna opens with something beautiful. He says 'My delusion is GONE.' After 10 chapters of Krishna explaining reality — Sankhya, Karma Yoga, Bhakti, Jnana, Vibhuti — Arjuna's fog has LIFTED. Like a student who struggled with calculus for an entire semester and then suddenly goes 'OH. I GET IT NOW.'\n\nNotice 'mad-anugrahāya' — out of compassion FOR ME. Arjuna acknowledges that Krishna taught not to lecture but because He CARED. Every great teacher's motivation is compassion, not ego. Your best professor was the one who stayed after class because they saw you were confused.\n\nArjuna says 'moha vigata' — delusion GONE. Not reduced, not managed — GONE. That is what genuine spiritual knowledge does. It does not give you coping mechanisms. It REMOVES the root confusion."
