          translation: "The Supreme Lord said: I am Time, the mighty destroyer of worlds, here engaged in destroying all people. Even without you, all the warriors standing in the opposing armies shall not survive.",
          modernInterpretation: "KĀLO'SMI. I AM TIME. Three syllables that changed the history of human thought. This is the verse Robert Oppenheimer quoted after the first atomic bomb test at Trinity: 'Now I am become Death, the destroyer of worlds.'\n\nKrishna does not say 'I am Love' or 'I am Light.' He says 'I am TIME — the DESTROYER.' Because that is the ultimate truth about the nature of reality. Everything that exists in time will be CONSUMED by time. Your body, your achievements, your empires, your memories — Time eats them ALL.\n\nBut then comes the LIBERATING truth: 'Even without you, these warriors will not survive.' Arjuna is NOT the cause of their death. Time is. The war's outcome is ALREADY decided. Arjuna is merely an instrument — a tool through which the inevitable becomes actual.\n\nThis is the deepest teaching on ACTION in the Gita. You are not the DOER. Time is doing everything. Your job is simply to be the instrument, to play your role, to do your duty — while understanding that the results were decided before you even picked up your bow."
