          translation: "Therefore arise, gain glory. Conquer your enemies and enjoy a prosperous kingdom. They have already been slain by Me. Be merely an instrument, O Savyasachin.",
          modernInterpretation: "NIMITTA-MĀTRAM BHAVA — Be merely an INSTRUMENT. This is arguably the most profound instruction in the entire Gita. Krishna says: 'I have ALREADY killed them. The work is DONE. You just need to show up and execute.'\n\nThink about what this means for YOUR life. Every outcome is already determined by the cosmic order. Your job is not to CONTROL results — your job is to be a good INSTRUMENT. A violin does not worry about whether the symphony will be beautiful. It simply lets the musician PLAY through it.\n\nUTTIṢṬHA — ARISE. The same command from Chapter 2, but now with a COMPLETELY different context. In Chapter 2, it was 'Get up and fight because it is your duty.' Now it is 'Get up and fight because the battle is ALREADY WON. You are just the delivery mechanism.'\n\nThe difference between anxiety and peace is this: anxiety says 'I must make this work.' Peace says 'The work is already done. I just need to be the instrument.' That shift — from doer to instrument — is the entire message of this verse."
