          translation: "Sanjaya said: Having heard these words of Krishna, the crowned Arjuna, trembling with folded hands, bowing down, spoke to Krishna in a faltering voice, greatly afraid.",
          modernInterpretation: "Sanjaya gives us the human reaction shot. Arjuna — the CROWNED one, the CHAMPION, the greatest archer alive — is TREMBLING. With FOLDED HANDS. Speaking in a FALTERING voice. 'Bhīta-bhītaḥ' — VERY MUCH afraid. The repetition of 'bhīta' emphasizes the depth of his terror.\n\nThis is the most powerful warrior in the world, reduced to a trembling, stammering devotee. And this is EXACTLY as it should be. When you truly encounter the Absolute, your ego does not just shrink — it SHATTERS. All your titles, achievements, and armor become tissue paper before the cosmic fire.\n\nThe beauty is — Arjuna does not RUN. He trembles, but he STAYS. He stammers, but he SPEAKS. He is afraid, but he BOWS. That is the definition of courage — not the absence of fear, but the willingness to bow DESPITE the fear."
