          translation: "Arjuna said: It is fitting, O Hrishikesha, that the world rejoices and is devoted to glorifying You. The demons flee in fear in all directions, and all the hosts of perfected beings bow to You.",
          modernInterpretation: "Even in his trembling state, Arjuna finds words of profound insight. He says 'STHĀNE' — it is FITTING. It is RIGHT. The world's devotion to You is not blind faith — it is the CORRECT response to reality. Joy is the natural response to the Divine. Fear is the natural response of evil before the Divine.\n\nLook at the two reactions: the GOOD rejoice and become devoted. The DEMONS flee in terror. Same form, two completely different responses. The Universal Form is like a mirror — what you see depends on what you ARE. The pure heart sees beauty and bows. The impure heart sees terror and runs.\n\nArjuna calls Krishna 'Hṛṣīkeśa' — master of the SENSES. Even while describing cosmic chaos, he reminds us that this infinite, terrifying form is actually the one who CONTROLS all perception. The one managing every eye, ear, tongue, and mind in the universe. The cosmic destroyer is also the intimate controller of your heartbeat."
