          modernInterpretation: "Arjuna now enters a PRAYER of stunning depth. He asks — why WOULDN'T everyone bow to You? You are greater than Brahma — the CREATOR himself. The one who CREATED the creator. The source behind the source.\n\nAnd then this incredible philosophical statement: You are SAT (existence), ASAT (non-existence), and TAT PARAM YAT — that which is BEYOND both. Not just what IS. Not just what IS NOT. But the thing that makes BOTH possible. The ground on which existence and non-existence both stand.\n\nThis is consciousness at its most expansive. Most people think reality is what exists. Philosophers add what does NOT exist. Krishna is BEYOND that entire framework."
