          modernInterpretation: "Arjuna bows from the FRONT. From BEHIND. From ALL SIDES. There is no direction from which he does not bow. Because there is no direction in which Krishna does NOT exist.\n\nAnd then the ultimate statement: 'TATO ASI SARVAḤ' — therefore You ARE everything. Not 'You are IN everything.' You ARE everything. The chair you sit on, the air you breathe, the thought you are thinking RIGHT NOW — it is all Krishna. There is nothing that is NOT God.\n\nThis is the pinnacle of non-dual vision born from the most intense dualistic devotion. Arjuna started by bowing TO God. Now he realizes there is nothing that is NOT God. The worshipper discovers that the worshipper, the worship, and the worshipped are all ONE."
