          translation: "You are the father of this world, of all that moves and does not move. You are its most worthy object of worship, the greatest teacher. None is equal to You in the three worlds — how then could anyone be greater, O incomparable one?",
          modernInterpretation: "Arjuna establishes the cosmic hierarchy once and for all. Krishna is the FATHER of everything. The most worthy of worship. The greatest GURU. And then the logical conclusion — if none is EQUAL, how can anyone be GREATER?\n\nThis is not flattery. This is mathematical certainty born from direct vision. Arjuna has SEEN the Universal Form. He has verified the data himself. And the conclusion is: there is NO competition. Zero. The idea of anything being 'greater than God' is a logical impossibility.\n\n'Apratima-prabhāva' — incomparable power. There is no BENCHMARK against which to measure Krishna. When something is truly infinite, all comparisons become meaningless. You cannot say 'infinity plus one' is bigger than infinity. Krishna breaks the scale."
