          translation: "Sanjaya said: Having spoken thus, Vasudeva showed His own form again. The great soul, assuming His gentle form once more, consoled the frightened Arjuna.",
          modernInterpretation: "The most TENDER moment in the Gita. Krishna — who just showed Himself as the all-consuming cosmic fire — gently returns to His familiar form and CONSOLES the trembling Arjuna. 'Saumya-vapuḥ' — the GENTLE form.\n\nImagine the contrast. One moment — a thousand suns, infinite mouths devouring worlds, the terrifying roar of cosmic dissolution. The next moment — the same person, smiling gently, probably putting a hand on Arjuna's shoulder, saying 'It is okay. I am here. The regular Me.'\n\nThis is God in totality. The one who CAN destroy everything CHOOSES to be gentle. Power restrained by love. Fire contained by friendship. The Universal Form could level the cosmos. But it CHOOSES to become a friend sitting on a chariot, consoling someone it loves."
