          modernInterpretation: "Arjuna can BREATHE again. 'Prakṛtim gataḥ' — returned to his own nature. Back to normal. The spiritual equivalent of a deep exhale after holding your breath for an eternity.\n\nNotice he calls the two-armed form 'mānuṣam' — HUMAN. Krishna's default form looks HUMAN. The infinite chose to look finite. The cosmic chose to look ordinary. The God of a trillion galaxies chose to look like a regular person. Because THAT is how He wants to be LOVED — not as a terrifying cosmic force, but as a person you can talk to, eat with, argue with, and ride a chariot with.\n\nArjuna is 'sa-cetāḥ' — with clear consciousness. The vision EXPANDED his awareness beyond breaking point. Now it has settled back. But it has settled into a DIFFERENT Arjuna. You cannot see infinity and come back unchanged. His normal is no longer the old normal. It is a DEEPER normal."
