          modernInterpretation: "Krishna repeats verse 48 to HAMMER the point home. No amount of KNOWLEDGE (Vedas), SUFFERING (austerity), GENEROSITY (charity), or RITUAL (sacrifice) can buy this ticket. The vision is NOT for sale.\n\nThis is the most DEMOCRATIZING statement in all of spirituality. It levels the playing field completely. The richest person cannot buy it. The most learned scholar cannot study their way to it. The most disciplined ascetic cannot suffer enough for it. And the most ritualistic priest cannot perform enough ceremonies.\n\nSo what DOES work? Krishna is about to tell us in the next two verses — and the answer will surprise everyone who thinks spirituality is about DOING more."
