          transliteration: "mayy eva mana ādhatsva mayi buddhiṁ niveśaya |\nnivasiṣyasi mayy eva ata ūrdhvaṁ na saṁśayaḥ ||8||",
          words: [
            { word: "मयि", transliteration: "mayi", meaning: "in Me" },
            { word: "एव", transliteration: "eva", meaning: "alone" },
            { word: "मनः", transliteration: "manaḥ", meaning: "mind" },
            { word: "आधत्स्व", transliteration: "ādhatsva", meaning: "fix/place" },
            { word: "मयि", transliteration: "mayi", meaning: "in Me" },
            { word: "बुद्धिम्", transliteration: "buddhim", meaning: "intellect" },
            { word: "निवेशय", transliteration: "niveśaya", meaning: "place/engage" },
            { word: "निवसिष्यसि", transliteration: "nivasiṣyasi", meaning: "you shall dwell" },
            { word: "मयि", transliteration: "mayi", meaning: "in Me" },
            { word: "एव", transliteration: "eva", meaning: "alone" },
            { word: "अतः ऊर्ध्वम्", transliteration: "ataḥ ūrdhvam", meaning: "hereafter" },
            { word: "न संशयः", transliteration: "na saṁśayaḥ", meaning: "no doubt" }
          ],
          translation: "Fix your mind on Me alone, place your intellect in Me. You shall then dwell in Me hereafter — of this there is no doubt.",
          modernInterpretation: "This is Step ONE of Krishna's FOUR-STEP devotion ladder — and it is the highest rung. He says: just fix your mind AND your intellect on Me. Mind (manas) is the emotional, feeling part — let it LOVE Me. Intellect (buddhi) is the rational, thinking part — let it UNDERSTAND Me. When both your heart and your head point in the same direction — toward the Divine — you do not just visit God. You DWELL in Him. 'Nivasiṣyasi mayy eva' — you will LIVE in Me.\n\nThink about what 'dwelling' means. A tourist visits a city — sees the sights, takes photos, leaves. A resident LIVES there. They know the back streets, the hidden chai shops, the sound of rain on the roof at 3 AM. Krishna is not asking you to be a spiritual tourist who visits Him during Navratri and Janmashtami. He is asking you to MOVE IN. Make His consciousness your permanent address.\n\nAnd the guarantee: 'na saṁśayaḥ' — NO DOUBT. Zero ambiguity. This is not a 'maybe' or an 'in most cases.' This is the Creator of the universe giving you His WORD. Fix your mind and intellect on Me, and you WILL dwell in Me. It is a LAW, not a suggestion. Like gravity — you do not negotiate with it. You do not need to believe in it for it to work. Just DO it, and the result follows automatically.\n\nBut Krishna knows this is HARD. Not everyone can just snap their fingers and fix their mind on God 24/7. So what comes next? The backup plan. And the backup plan's backup plan. Because Krishna does not just set a high bar — He builds a STAIRCASE to help you reach it."
