          translation: "But those who follow this immortal nectar of dharma as I have declared, endowed with faith, regarding Me as supreme — those devotees are exceedingly dear to Me.",
          modernInterpretation: "And HERE is the grand finale. The last verse of Chapter 12. And Krishna does not just say 'priyaḥ' — dear. He says 'ATĪVA me priyāḥ' — EXCEEDINGLY dear. SUPREMELY dear. Beyond-words dear. He has been saying 'dear to Me' throughout this chapter, but for the final verse, He turns the volume up to MAXIMUM.\n\nWhat makes these devotees so special? They follow 'dharmyāmṛtam' — the NECTAR of dharma. Not just dharma. AMṚTA — nectar, the drink of IMMORTALITY. Krishna is saying that everything He has described in this chapter — the equanimity, the compassion, the contentment, the freedom from ego — is not bitter medicine. It is NECTAR. It is the sweetest thing you will ever taste. The qualities of a devotee are not BURDENS to carry — they are GIFTS to unwrap.\n\n'Yathoktam' — as I have DECLARED. Not as some guru interprets it. Not as some trending influencer repackages it. As KRISHNA Himself has said it. Straight from the source. No middlemen. No dilution.\n\n'Śraddadhānāḥ' — with FAITH. Not blind faith. Not superstitious faith. But the deep, soul-level TRUST that comes from having HEARD the truth, CONTEMPLATED the truth, and FELT the truth resonate in your bones.\n\n'Mat-paramāḥ' — regarding ME as the SUPREME goal. Not as one goal among many. Not as Plan B if the career does not work out. THE goal. The ONLY goal. Everything else is a means to this one end.\n\nAnd so Chapter 12 closes. The shortest chapter in the Gita. Only 20 verses. But in these 20 verses, Krishna has done something extraordinary. He has told us that the path of DEVOTION is the highest. He has given us a FOUR-STEP staircase for when devotion feels hard. And He has painted the most COMPLETE portrait of an ideal human being ever composed — not a list of rituals to perform, but a list of QUALITIES to embody. Compassion, contentment, equanimity, selflessness, skill, purity, steadiness. THIS is what God loves. Not your temple donations. Not your social media spirituality. YOUR CHARACTER. The way you treat the watchman at your building. The way you handle criticism. The way you respond when life does not go your way. THAT is your real prayer. THAT is your true worship. And THAT is what makes you EXCEEDINGLY dear to the Divine."
