          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just listed FIVE job titles for the Supreme Soul sitting inside your body. Upadrashta — the WITNESS who watches everything silently like that one friend in the group who sees all the drama but says nothing. Anumanta — the PERMITTER who allows things to happen, like a parent letting a toddler make mistakes so they learn. Bharta — the SUSTAINER who keeps the whole show running, like that one person in every Indian family who quietly pays all the bills. Bhokta — the EXPERIENCER. And Maheshvara — the SUPREME LORD.\n\nSo let me get this straight — God is not sitting in some far-off heaven judging you from a distance. He is RIGHT THERE inside you, closer than your own heartbeat, watching, permitting, sustaining. He is not your Swiggy delivery guy who comes and goes. He is your ROOMMATE. He is with you 24/7.\n\nAnd He is called PARAMATMA — the Supreme Self — different from your individual atma. Think of it like this: your atma is like a single Wi-Fi device, and the Paramatma is the ROUTER. Every device has its own identity, but they are all connected to and sustained by the same source. You are never truly ALONE. The Paramatma is always watching, always supporting, always there. That is not surveillance — that is LOVE."
