          modernInterpretation: "This is the ULTIMATE promise. Krishna says if you truly understand three things — Purusha (the soul), Prakriti (material nature), and the three gunas (sattva, rajas, tamas) — you are DONE. No more rebirths. No more coming back to deal with Mumbai traffic, board exams, and relatives asking about your salary. You are FREE.\n\nAnd the beautiful part is — 'sarvathā vartamānaḥ api' — REGARDLESS of your current situation. You could be a CEO or a chai-wallah. You could be in an ashram or in Andheri West sharing a 1BHK with four roommates. Your current CIRCUMSTANCES do not matter. What matters is your UNDERSTANDING.\n\nThis is so liberating. Krishna is not saying you need to renounce everything, go to the Himalayas, grow a beard, and eat roots. He is saying you can be RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE — stuck in a 9-to-5, commuting in a packed metro, dealing with your in-laws — and if you TRULY understand the Purusha-Prakriti-Guna framework, you are liberated. It is not about changing your LOCATION. It is about changing your UNDERSTANDING. The jail is not the body, the jail is IGNORANCE. And knowledge is the key that opens EVERY lock."
