          modernInterpretation: "THIS verse is why the Gita is the most INCLUSIVE spiritual text ever written. Krishna is saying there is NOT just one way to find God. Some people meditate — they sit quietly, go inward, and find the truth through DHYANA. Some people use KNOWLEDGE — they read, analyse, debate, use their intellect like a laser beam to cut through illusion. That is Sankhya Yoga. And some people? They just DO WORK — selflessly, without attachment — and through that karma, they find the divine.\n\nThink about it. In a class of 60 students, does everyone learn the same way? Some are visual learners. Some learn by doing. Some need to hear it explained. A GOOD teacher does not force one method. And Krishna is the GREATEST teacher. He says, 'Pick your path. Whatever works for YOUR nature.'\n\nThis is why Hinduism never had religious wars about methodology. You want to meditate? Great. You want to study scriptures? Fantastic. You want to serve the poor and call that your worship? EQUALLY valid. It is like reaching Mumbai — you can take a flight, a train, or drive. You can even WALK if you are that hardcore. The destination is the same. Krishna does not care about your MODE of transport. He cares that you are MOVING. So stop judging the meditator if you are a karma yogi, and stop looking down on the worker if you are a jnani. Everyone has their route. RESPECT it."
