          modernInterpretation: "This verse is Krishna's SAFETY NET for everyone who thinks 'But I am not a yogi, I am not a scholar, I do not even know how to meditate properly.' Krishna says EVEN if you do not know any of the three paths — meditation, knowledge, or karma yoga — if you simply LISTEN to someone who knows and follow their guidance with faith, YOU ALSO cross beyond death.\n\nThis is HUGE. This means your grandmother who cannot read Sanskrit but listens to Bhagavat Katha with full devotion on the TV — she is covered. That auto driver who has a small Gita in his dashboard and listens to pravachans on YouTube while waiting for passengers — he is covered. You do not need a PhD in Vedanta. You need EARS and FAITH.\n\nShruti-parayana — devoted to LISTENING. In our culture, SHRAVANAM (listening) has always been the first step of learning. Before you read, before you practise, you LISTEN. That is why satsang exists. That is why pravachans exist. That is why your dadi keeps forcing you to sit during the evening aarti — because just HEARING sacred words, even without fully understanding them, creates TRANSFORMATION. It is like music. You do not need to understand the raaga to be moved by it. The vibration does the work. Just SHOW UP and LISTEN. Krishna will handle the rest."
