          translation: "Whatever being is born, whether moving or unmoving, know that it arises from the union of the Field (Kshetra) and the Knower of the Field (Kshetrajna), O best of the Bharatas.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just gave you the FORMULA for all of creation. Every single thing that exists — from the banyan tree standing still for 500 years to the sparrow flying past your window to your neighbour's annoying dog that barks at 3 AM — ALL of it exists because of the UNION of Kshetra (the field/matter) and Kshetrajna (the knower/consciousness). Body plus soul. Hardware plus software. Without the body, the soul has no vehicle. Without the soul, the body is just a lump of organic matter.\n\nThis is literally the recipe for ALL life. Take some Prakriti (matter), add some consciousness (Purusha), mix well — boom, you have a living being. A plant? Kshetra plus Kshetrajna. An ant? Same formula. A whale? Same formula. Elon Musk? SAME formula. The ingredients are identical — what differs is the PROPORTION and complexity of the field.\n\nThis should make you see EVERY living being differently. That stray dog on the road? Kshetra-Kshetrajna samyoga. That tree you walk past without noticing? Same divine combination. The cockroach you are about to smash with a chappal? Consciousness is INSIDE that too. This is not tree-hugging hippie philosophy. This is the PHYSICS of existence as described by the Supreme Being Himself."
