          modernInterpretation: "YAH PASHYATI SA PASHYATI. He who SEES, truly SEES. This might be the most powerful line in all of Chapter 13. Krishna is redefining what it means to have VISION. Most of us think seeing means using our eyes. But Krishna says real seeing is perceiving the IMPERISHABLE Supreme Lord dwelling EQUALLY in ALL perishable beings.\n\nEQUALLY. Not more in a Brahmin, less in a Shudra. Not more in a human, less in an animal. Not more in a rich person, less in a beggar. EQUALLY. Same Wi-Fi signal strength everywhere. Same divine presence in the IAS officer and the watchman. Same Paramatma in the peacock and the pigeon.\n\nAnd here is the mind-bending part — this imperishable Lord exists in things that ARE perishing. The body is dying every second — cells are replacing, aging is happening, entropy is doing its thing. But INSIDE this constantly decaying vehicle, something INDESTRUCTIBLE sits calmly. It is like finding a diamond inside a mud pot. The pot will break, but the diamond does not care.\n\nSo the next time you judge someone by their body, their clothes, their caste, their Instagram followers — remember: you are judging the MUD POT. The diamond inside is IDENTICAL in everyone. The one who sees THAT — sa pashyati — THAT person truly sees."
