          modernInterpretation: "This is the PRACTICAL benefit of the vision described in the previous verse. When you see God equally in everyone, what happens? You stop DESTROYING yourself. 'Na hinasti atmanam atmana' — you do not degrade yourself BY yourself.\n\nThink about it — how do we destroy ourselves? Through hatred, jealousy, cruelty, arrogance. And WHERE do these come from? From seeing DIFFERENCES. 'He is better than me' — jealousy. 'She is lower than me' — arrogance. 'They are different from me' — hatred. ALL self-destruction comes from seeing INEQUALITY where there is actually EQUALITY.\n\nBut the moment you see Ishvara equally in the beggar and the billionaire, in the crow and the peacock, in your friend and your enemy — ALL those toxic emotions lose their FUEL. You cannot hate someone when you see God in them. You cannot be arrogant when you see the same God in everyone, including those you consider 'below' you.\n\nAnd the result? PARAM GATIM — the supreme destination. Not some average moksha. The HIGHEST goal. The VIP lounge of spiritual achievement. And the ticket? Not expensive rituals or extreme austerity. Just EQUAL VISION. See God everywhere. That is it. The hardest simple thing you will ever do."
