          translation: "Just as the all-pervading space is not tainted because of its subtlety, so the Self, though situated everywhere in the body, is not tainted.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna gives the PERFECT analogy. Space — aakaash — is EVERYWHERE. It is inside your room, inside a garbage dump, inside a palace, inside a sewer. But does space ever become DIRTY? Does the space inside a dustbin start smelling? No. Because space is too SUBTLE to be affected by gross things. Smoke may fill a room, but the space itself is untouched. Remove the smoke, and the space is exactly as it was.\n\nYour ATMA is like that. It is inside the body, which gets sick, which ages, which does embarrassing things, which sometimes eats too much paneer tikka at weddings. But the atma inside? UNTOUCHED. Your body commits a mistake — the atma is not stained. Your mind has negative thoughts — the atma is not corrupted. Your ego gets bruised — the atma does not even notice.\n\nThis is such a freeing realisation. We spend our ENTIRE lives thinking we are damaged, broken, sinful, not good enough. Therapy bills, self-help books, motivation seminars — all because we think something is WRONG with us. But Krishna says the REAL you — the atma — has NEVER been damaged. Not once. Not ever. You are not broken. You are space pretending to be the room. And space cannot break. You just need to remember WHAT you are. That is the whole game."
