          translation: "Just as the one sun illuminates this entire world, so the Lord of the Field (the Soul) illuminates the entire field (the body), O Bharata.",
          modernInterpretation: "What a STUNNING analogy. One sun — EKAH RAVIH — lights up the ENTIRE world. Not multiple suns for different countries. Not a separate sun for India and another for America. ONE sun. Similarly, ONE atma illuminates the ENTIRE body. Your eyes see because the atma's consciousness powers them. Your ears hear because the atma is behind them. Your brain thinks because the atma's awareness activates it. Remove the atma, and the body is a corpse — all the organs are there, all the neurons are there, but there is NO light.\n\nThis is why a dead body cannot see even though it has eyes. The hardware is intact, but the POWER SOURCE is gone. The atma was the electricity, and now the building is dark.\n\nAnd notice — the sun illuminates WITHOUT being affected by what it illuminates. The sun shines on a temple and a toilet equally. The sun does not become holy by shining on a temple or dirty by shining on a gutter. Similarly, the atma illuminates all the body's activities — good and bad — without being affected. Your body does something noble? The atma illuminates it. Your body does something shameful? The atma illuminates that too. But like the sun, it remains PURE. It is just the light source. It does not become what it illuminates."
