      summary: "Chapter 14 unveils the three fundamental forces that govern ALL of material existence — Sattva (goodness, light, knowledge), Rajas (passion, activity, restlessness), and Tamas (darkness, inertia, ignorance). Krishna explains how these three gunas are born from Prakriti and bind the immortal soul to the mortal body like invisible chains — sattva binds through attachment to happiness and knowledge, rajas through attachment to action and craving, and tamas through negligence, delusion, and sleep. He describes the signs of each guna's dominance, what happens at death when each prevails, and ultimately reveals the way BEYOND all three — unwavering devotion to the Supreme. The one who transcends the gunas attains the nectar of immortality.",
