          translation: "The Supreme Lord said: I shall again declare that supreme knowledge, the best of all knowledge, having known which all the sages have attained the highest perfection from this world.",
          modernInterpretation: "Welcome to Chapter 14, folks — GUNATRAYA VIBHAGA YOGA — The Yoga of the Three Gunas. And Krishna opens with what is essentially the ULTIMATE sales pitch. He says, 'I am going to tell you the BEST knowledge there is — the KNOWLEDGE of all knowledges.' Not good knowledge. Not great knowledge. UTTAMAM — the SUPREME knowledge. The kind of knowledge that every sage who ever existed used to reach PERFECTION.\n\nThink about it. If someone told you, 'I know the one thing that every successful person in history knew — every Buddha, every Rishi, every enlightened being — and I am about to tell you for FREE,' would you not lean in? That is exactly what Krishna is doing. He is saying this knowledge is so powerful that EVERYONE who has ever truly understood it has achieved the highest state of existence. Not some of them. ALL of them. A 100% success rate. No coaching institute in Kota can promise that.\n\nAnd notice He says 'BHUYAH' — AGAIN. This is not the first time He is sharing deep knowledge. He has been dropping wisdom since Chapter 2. But He keeps coming back to say, 'Wait, there is MORE.' It is like a TV show that keeps getting better each season. Chapter 13 was about the field and the knower. Now Chapter 14 is about the three FORCES that operate within that field. If Chapter 13 gave you the MAP, Chapter 14 gives you the WEATHER REPORT. And trust me, you NEED to know the weather before you step outside."
