          translation: "By taking refuge in this knowledge and attaining My nature, they are not born again even at the time of creation, nor are they disturbed at the time of dissolution.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna just raised the stakes to INFINITY. He says, 'Those who truly grasp this knowledge attain MY nature — SADHARMYAM — and after that, they are not reborn even when the entire UNIVERSE is created again, and they are not destroyed even when the entire universe DISSOLVES.' That is not just moksha. That is PERMANENT cosmic VIP status.\n\nLet that sink in. Hindu cosmology talks about cycles — Srishti (creation) and Pralaya (dissolution). The universe is born, lives, dies, and is reborn. Like a cosmic heartbeat. Even the GODS are recycled in this process. But the one who has this knowledge? They are EXEMPT. They have stepped OFF the merry-go-round entirely. No more birth at creation time. No more panic at destruction time. They have merged with Krishna's own nature.\n\nIt is like the difference between being a CHARACTER in a video game and being the DEVELOPER. Characters live and die when the game runs and resets. But the developer? The developer exists OUTSIDE the game. Creation and destruction are just buttons on their keyboard. Krishna is saying, 'Learn what I am about to teach you, and you graduate from PLAYER to DEVELOPER.' That is the promise of Chapter 14."
