          translation: "The great Brahman (material nature) is My womb. In that I place the seed. From that, O Bharata, is the birth of all living beings.",
          modernInterpretation: "This is one of the most PROFOUND cosmological verses in the entire Gita. Krishna describes the creation of the universe as a cosmic act of CONCEPTION. MAHAD BRAHMA — the great material nature — is the WOMB. And Krishna places the GARBHA — the seed of consciousness — into it. From this union, ALL living beings are born.\n\nThink of it like this — Prakriti (material nature) is like the HARDWARE of the universe. The atoms, molecules, elements, forces — all the raw material. But raw material alone does not produce LIFE. You need SOFTWARE — consciousness, awareness, the spark of existence. Krishna is the one who INSTALLS the software into the hardware. Without Him, Prakriti is just dead matter floating in space. With His seed of consciousness, suddenly there are BEINGS — ants, trees, humans, galaxies of living things.\n\nThis is also a radical verse because Krishna is calling Himself the FATHER of all creation. Not the father of just humans. Not the father of just Hindus. The father of ALL living beings — sarva-bhutanam. Every creature that has ever existed or will ever exist traces its origin to this one act — Krishna placing the seed of consciousness into the womb of material nature. THAT is the moment the universe became ALIVE."
