          translation: "Whatever forms are produced in all the wombs, O son of Kunti, the great Brahman (material nature) is their womb, and I am the seed-giving father.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna makes it CRYSTAL clear now. He says, 'Every form of life — in EVERY species, in EVERY womb — whatever body takes shape anywhere in creation — the MOTHER is Prakriti (material nature), and the FATHER is ME.' BIJA-PRADAH PITA — I am the seed-giving father. This is Krishna declaring cosmic PARENTHOOD.\n\nThe implications are STAGGERING. That dog on the street? Krishna is its father. That mosquito buzzing around your ear at 3 AM? Same father. That tree in your garden? Same father. The bacteria in your gut? Same father. Krishna does not discriminate between species. He does not say 'I am the father of humans' or 'I am the father of the devatas.' He says SARVA-YONISHU — in ALL wombs. Every living being is His child.\n\nIf you TRULY internalize this, your entire relationship with the world changes. You cannot look at ANY creature with contempt anymore. That stray cat is your sibling. That earthworm in the mud is your sibling. We all share the same FATHER — Krishna — and the same MOTHER — Prakriti. This is not some feel-good environmentalist slogan. This is ONTOLOGICAL truth according to the Gita. We are literally ONE FAMILY. Vasudhaiva Kutumbakam is not just a nice saying — it is a SCIENTIFIC FACT of spiritual cosmology."
