          modernInterpretation: "Krishna gives you a DIAGNOSTIC TOOL. He says, 'Want to know if sattva is dominant in you right now? Check if LIGHT is shining through all your senses.' SARVA-DVARESHU — through ALL the gates of the body. The gates are your senses — eyes, ears, nose, mouth, skin, and mind.\n\nWhen sattva is dominant, your eyes see BEAUTY in ordinary things. Your ears hear MEANING in words. Your mind grasps CONCEPTS with clarity. Everything feels BRIGHT, not because the external world changed, but because YOUR internal lens is clean. It is like cleaning a dirty window — the sun was always shining, but now you can actually SEE it.\n\nYou know those rare mornings when you wake up and everything just MAKES SENSE? When you feel sharp, focused, grateful, and somehow the same commute that usually annoys you feels peaceful? That is sattva being VIVRUDDHA — increased, dominant. Your perception is not clouded by desire (rajas) or delusion (tamas). You are seeing things AS THEY ARE. This is why ancient rishis recommended sattvic food, sattvic company, sattvic environments — not because they were health freaks, but because they understood that your INNER state determines your OUTER experience. The world does not change. YOUR guna changes. And everything follows."
