          modernInterpretation: "Now Krishna gives you the RAJAS CHECKLIST. Five symptoms: LOBHA (greed — wanting more), PRAVRITTI (constant activity — cannot sit still), ARAMBHA (always starting new projects), ASHAMA (restlessness — inner unease), and SPRIHA (craving — longing for things you do not have). If you have three or more of these right now, congratulations — rajas is running your operating system.\n\nDoes this sound familiar? It should. Because this is the DEFAULT MODE of modern civilization. The entire global economy runs on rajas. Advertising creates SPRIHA (longing). Capitalism rewards PRAVRITTI (activity). Startup culture celebrates ARAMBHA (starting things). Social media amplifies ASHAMA (restlessness). And the whole system is fueled by LOBHA (greed). We have built an ENTIRE WORLD on rajasic energy and then wonder why everyone is anxious and burned out.\n\nNotice Krishna does not say rajas is EVIL. He says these things JĀYANTE — they ARISE. It is just what happens when rajas is dominant. Like how rain happens when clouds gather. It is not moral judgment — it is METEOROLOGY of the soul. But if you are AWARE that rajas is dominant, you can take steps. You can slow down. You can question your cravings. You can ask, 'Do I REALLY need this, or is rajas just doing its thing?' Awareness is the first step toward CHOICE."
