          translation: "From Sattva arises knowledge, from Rajas arises greed, and from Tamas arise negligence, delusion, and ignorance.",
          modernInterpretation: "This verse is the CAUSAL chain. Krishna is not just telling you the symptoms anymore — He is telling you the OFFSPRING of each guna. Sattva PRODUCES knowledge. Rajas PRODUCES greed. Tamas PRODUCES negligence, delusion, and ignorance. Each guna is a FACTORY and these are its products.\n\nThink about what you PRODUCE in your daily life. When you are sattvic — after a good meditation, a meaningful conversation, deep study — what comes out of you? INSIGHT. Understanding. Wisdom. Ideas that help people. But when rajas takes over — after hours on social media, after comparing yourself to others — what comes out? GREED. Wanting what others have. Planning how to get MORE. And when tamas is in charge — after a week of junk food, zero exercise, and mindless entertainment — what comes out? CONFUSION. Bad decisions. Inability to think clearly.\n\nYour INPUT determines your OUTPUT. Sattvic inputs (good food, good books, good company) produce knowledge. Rajasic inputs (competitive environments, materialistic goals, constant stimulation) produce greed. Tamasic inputs (junk food, toxic media, inactivity) produce ignorance. This is not philosophy — it is ENGINEERING. You are a MACHINE, and the gunas are the FUEL. Put premium fuel in, you get premium performance. Put garbage in, you get garbage out. Krishna figured out GIGO — Garbage In, Garbage Out — five thousand years before computer science."
