          modernInterpretation: "THIS is the TURNING POINT of the entire chapter. Krishna says, 'When a person TRULY sees that the gunas alone are the doers of ALL actions — and simultaneously knows that the SELF is BEYOND the gunas — that person attains MY nature.' Two realizations in one. First: the gunas are doing everything. Second: the real YOU is beyond them.\n\nThis is LIBERATION IN ONE VERSE. Think about what happens when you get angry. Usually you say, 'I am angry.' But Krishna says the TRUTH is: 'Rajas guna is activated in this body-mind system.' When you feel lazy: 'Tamas guna is dominant right now.' When you feel peaceful: 'Sattva guna is currently in charge.' The real YOU — the DRASHTA, the witness, the seer — is NONE of these. You are the one WATCHING all three gunas perform their dance.\n\nIt is like watching a movie. The screen shows action scenes (rajas), dark horror scenes (tamas), and beautiful serene landscapes (sattva). But the SCREEN itself is none of these. The screen is unchanged regardless of what movie plays. YOU are the screen. The gunas are the movie. When you TRULY get this — not intellectually but EXPERIENTIALLY — when you can watch anger arise and think 'Oh, rajas is acting up' instead of 'I AM angry' — that is when you attain MAD-BHAVA, Krishna's own nature. You step out of the movie and realize you were the screen all along."
