          modernInterpretation: "Krishna reveals the ULTIMATE PRIZE. Transcend all three gunas and you become FREE from the four fundamental sufferings — JANMA (birth), MRITYU (death), JARA (old age), and DUHKHA (sorrow). And what do you GET instead? AMRITAM — immortality. Not just a long life. DEATHLESSNESS. The nectar of eternal existence.\n\nNotice He says the gunas are DEHA-SAMUDBHAVAN — they arise from the BODY. They are not part of the soul. They are like weather patterns — clouds form, rain falls, sun shines — but the SKY itself is untouched by all of it. The sky does not get wet when it rains. The sky does not burn when the sun blazes. Similarly, your soul does not become sattvic, rajasic, or tamasic. Only your body-mind complex does. Transcendence means REMEMBERING this permanently.\n\nThis verse is the MISSION STATEMENT of all spiritual practice. Why do we meditate? To transcend the gunas. Why do we study scripture? To transcend the gunas. Why do we practice detachment? To transcend the gunas. Every spiritual tool ever invented has ONE goal — to help you step BEYOND these three modes and taste AMRITA, the nectar of your own immortal nature. Birth, death, old age, sorrow — these are not inevitable for the SOUL. They are inevitable only for one who is IDENTIFIED with the gunas. Dis-identify, and you are free. PERMANENTLY."
