          translation: "Its branches spread below and above, nourished by the three gunas, with sense objects as its buds. Its roots also extend downward in the human world, bound by the results of actions (karma).",
          modernInterpretation: "Now Krishna ZOOMS IN on this cosmic tree and shows you the DETAILS. The branches spread in ALL directions — upward to the higher realms, downward to the lower ones. And what FEEDS these branches? The three gunas — sattva, rajas, and tamas. Your goodness, your ambition, your laziness — all of these are NUTRIENTS for this tree. Every quality you possess is making this tree grow BIGGER and more complex.\n\nThe BUDS and SHOOTS of this tree? They are SENSE OBJECTS. Your desire for good food, beautiful sights, pleasant music, comfortable touch, nice fragrances — every sensory craving is a tiny new leaf sprouting on this tree. Every time you scroll Instagram and feel a pull, that is a new bud growing. Every time you crave that midnight biryani, another shoot appears. The tree keeps growing because YOU keep watering it with desire.\n\nBut here is the REALLY scary part — the tree also has SECONDARY ROOTS that grow DOWNWARD into the human world, and these roots are KARMA. Your actions in this life create new attachments that bind you further. It is like a banyan tree that drops aerial roots from its branches, and those roots become new trunks, and those trunks grow new branches, and those branches drop more roots. It NEVER ends. You do something, it creates consequences, those consequences drive new actions, and the cycle continues. You are trapped inside a self-replicating tree of existence, and most people do not even realize they are inside it."
