          translation: "I am seated in the hearts of all beings. From Me come memory, knowledge, and the removal of doubts. I alone am to be known by all the Vedas. I am the author of Vedanta and the knower of the Vedas.",
          modernInterpretation: "This is one of the most COMPREHENSIVE self-declarations Krishna makes in the entire Gita. Let us unpack it layer by layer because every single phrase is a BOMBSHELL.\n\n'Sarvasya cha aham hridi sannivishtah' — I am seated in the heart of ALL beings. Not just devotees. Not just good people. Not just humans. ALL beings. The saint and the sinner. The scholar and the criminal. The ant and the elephant. God is not somewhere far away in a heaven — He is INSIDE you, right now, sitting in your heart. Closer than your own HEARTBEAT.\n\n'Mattah smritir jnanam apohanam cha' — From Me come MEMORY, KNOWLEDGE, and FORGETFULNESS. Wait — FORGETFULNESS? Why would God give us forgetfulness? Because sometimes you NEED to forget. If you remembered every trauma of every past life, you would be PARALYZED. Forgetfulness is a MERCY. Knowledge reveals what you need to know. Memory preserves what you have learned. Forgetfulness removes what would DESTROY you. All three are divine FUNCTIONS managed by Krishna from inside your heart.\n\n'Vedais cha sarvair aham eva vedyah' — I alone am to be known through all the Vedas. EVERY sacred text, every scripture, every hymn, every mantra — they are ALL trying to point you to ONE reality: Krishna. The Vedas are not about rituals. They are not about philosophy. They are about KNOWING HIM.\n\nAnd the grand finale — 'Vedanta-krit veda-vid eva cha aham' — I am the AUTHOR of Vedanta and the KNOWER of the Vedas. He WROTE the textbook AND He is the only one who fully UNDERSTANDS it. The creator of the curriculum is also the only one who has MASTERED it. Everyone else is still a student. Even the greatest scholars are just reading HIS book."
