          modernInterpretation: "Now we arrive at the HEART of this chapter — the reason it is called PURUSHOTTAMA Yoga. Krishna begins laying out a cosmic CLASSIFICATION system that is breathtaking in its simplicity.\n\nTwo kinds of purusha exist in this world. First — KSHARA, the perishable. This includes EVERYTHING that is created, everything that has a form, everything that changes. Your body, your thoughts, your relationships, your career, your country, the earth itself, the stars, the galaxies — ALL of it is kshara. ALL of it will eventually perish. Every single thing you can point to and say 'THAT exists' — it is temporary.\n\nSecond — AKSHARA, the imperishable. This is the KUTASTHA — the unchanging, immovable reality. Think of it as the SCREEN on which the movie of creation plays. Characters come and go, scenes change, plots twist — but the screen remains UNCHANGED. The akshara purusha is the eternal substratum, the unchanging consciousness that remains constant while everything else dances and dissolves.\n\nIn your daily life, you experience BOTH. Your body ages — that is kshara. Your awareness of 'I exist' never changes — that is akshara. Your emotions fluctuate wildly — kshara. The WITNESS behind those emotions remains perfectly still — akshara. You were a baby, a teenager, an adult — your form changed completely. But the SENSE of being you? That has never changed. That is the akshara in you.\n\nBut Krishna is about to drop the REAL bombshell — because there is a THIRD category that transcends both of these. Stay tuned."
