          modernInterpretation: "This verse is the PAYOFF of the entire chapter. Krishna says — whoever understands what I just explained, whoever GETS IT without delusion, that person becomes a SARVA-VIT — a knower of EVERYTHING. Not someone who has read every book. Not someone who has a PhD in philosophy. Someone who knows KRISHNA AS PURUSHOTTAMA. Because if you know the SOURCE of everything, you effectively know EVERYTHING.\n\nIt is like knowing the seed of a banyan tree. If you truly understand the SEED, you understand the bark, the branches, the leaves, the aerial roots, the entire forest that one tree can become. Know the SOURCE, and you know all that flows from it.\n\nAnd what does this person DO with this knowledge? 'Bhajati mam sarva-bhavena' — they worship Me with their WHOLE BEING. Not partial devotion. Not Sunday-morning devotion. Not 'I will pray when I am in trouble' devotion. SARVA-BHAVENA — with every fiber of their existence. Their thinking is worship. Their breathing is worship. Their working is worship. Their sleeping is worship. Every single aspect of their being is oriented toward Krishna like a compass needle toward magnetic north.\n\nThis is the difference between KNOWING ABOUT God and KNOWING God. You can know about Krishna from a textbook. But when you KNOW Krishna as Purushottama — not intellectually but EXPERIENTIALLY, not partially but COMPLETELY — then your entire life becomes an act of devotion. You do not PRACTICE worship. You BECOME worship. Every cell in your body is singing, every thought is a prayer, every action is an offering. That is sarva-bhavena bhajati. And THAT is the goal of this entire chapter."
