          modernInterpretation: "Welcome to Chapter 16, everyone. DAIVASURA SAMPAD VIBHAGA YOGA — the chapter where Krishna literally gives you a SCORECARD to figure out whether you are playing for Team Divine or Team Demonic. No ambiguity. No grey areas. Just a straight-up CHARACTER AUDIT.\n\nAnd He starts with the DIVINE qualities. First on the list? ABHAYAM — FEARLESSNESS. Not recklessness, not bravado, not that fake confidence you put on before a job interview. Real fearlessness — the kind that comes from KNOWING who you truly are. When you realize you are the eternal soul and not this temporary body, what is left to fear? Death? Already handled. Failure? Just a costume change. Public opinion? Noise from other temporary bodies.\n\nThen comes PURITY OF HEART — not just taking a bath and doing puja, but cleaning the INSIDE. Your intentions, your motives, the stories you tell yourself when nobody is watching. Then CHARITY — not the Instagram-post-with-a-poor-kid kind, but genuine giving without expecting a thank you. SELF-CONTROL, SACRIFICE, STUDY, AUSTERITY, SIMPLICITY. Notice that Krishna is not listing ACHIEVEMENTS here. He is listing CHARACTER TRAITS. He does not say 'be rich, be famous, be powerful.' He says 'be fearless, be pure, be generous.' The Gita's success metrics are RADICALLY different from LinkedIn's."
