          translation: "Non-violence, truthfulness, freedom from anger, renunciation, tranquility, aversion to fault-finding, compassion towards all beings, freedom from greed, gentleness, modesty, and steadiness —",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna continues the divine qualities list, and honestly, this verse alone could be the ENTIRE self-help section of any bookstore. AHIMSA — non-violence. Not just 'don't hit people,' but non-violence in thought, word, and deed. That sarcastic comment you are about to type on Twitter? Violence. That judgmental thought about your colleague? Violence. Ahimsa goes DEEP.\n\nSATYAM — truth. Not the 'brutal honesty' people use as an excuse to be cruel, but truth spoken with compassion and wisdom. AKRODHA — freedom from anger. Not suppressing anger like a pressure cooker, but genuinely not GENERATING it because you understand that the person annoying you is also just a soul struggling through their own karma.\n\nBut here is the REAL gem — APAISHUNAM. Aversion to fault-finding. How many of us spend our ENTIRE social life pointing out what is wrong with OTHER people? 'Did you see what she posted?' 'Can you believe he said that?' Krishna is saying — STOP. That habit of finding faults in others? That is NOT a divine quality. That is a DEMONIC tendency dressed up as social commentary.\n\nAnd then COMPASSION towards ALL beings — not just humans, not just your pet, not just cute animals on Instagram. ALL beings. The mosquito. The cockroach. The annoying neighbor. Krishna's compassion has NO filter and NO boundary."
