          modernInterpretation: "Krishna wraps up the divine qualities list and drops the summary. TEJAS — vigor, brilliance, inner fire. Not aggression, but that GLOW that comes from living with purpose and integrity. You know those people who walk into a room and something just SHIFTS? That is tejas. It is not charisma manufactured by a personality coach — it is the natural radiance of a clean conscience and a focused mind.\n\nKSHAMA — forgiveness. And this is a BIG one. Forgiveness is not saying 'what you did was okay.' It is saying 'I am not going to carry YOUR poison in MY bloodstream anymore.' It is the ultimate act of SELF-LIBERATION. Every grudge you hold is a chain YOU wear, not the other person.\n\nAnd then Krishna ties it all up — these are the DAIVI SAMPAD, the divine wealth. Notice the word SAMPAD — wealth. Krishna is REDEFINING what it means to be rich. In the world's dictionary, wealth equals money, property, followers, influence. In Krishna's dictionary, wealth equals fearlessness, truthfulness, compassion, forgiveness, and humility. If you have these qualities, you are a BILLIONAIRE in the spiritual economy. If you have a billion dollars but lack these qualities, you are BANKRUPT where it actually matters.\n\nTwenty-six qualities across three verses. That is your divine checklist. Not a single one requires a degree, a bank balance, or a social media following. Every single one is available to you RIGHT NOW, for FREE. The question is — are you investing in the right portfolio?"
