          modernInterpretation: "NOW we flip the coin. After 26 divine qualities spread across three verses, Krishna lists the DEMONIC qualities in just SIX words. And honestly? These six words describe about 80% of what you see on the internet every single day.\n\nDAMBHA — hypocrisy. Saying one thing, doing another. Posting about mental health awareness while bullying people in DMs. Talking about honesty while cooking your expense reports. Hypocrisy is the FOUNDATION of the demonic nature because everything else is built on this — the gap between who you PRETEND to be and who you ACTUALLY are.\n\nDARPA — arrogance. Not confidence, not competence — ARROGANCE. The belief that you are inherently BETTER than others. That your caste, your degree, your salary, your car makes you SUPERIOR. ABHIMANA — excessive pride, the kind that makes you unable to say 'I was wrong' or 'I do not know.' KRODHA — anger. PARUSHYA — harshness, cruelty in speech. And AJNANA — ignorance, not just lack of knowledge, but the REFUSAL to learn.\n\nNotice something? Krishna needed THREE verses for divine qualities and ONE verse for demonic ones. Why? Because destruction is always simpler than creation. It takes years to build a reputation and one tweet to destroy it. It takes decades to build trust and one lie to shatter it. The demonic path is EASY — that is exactly why so many people are on it."
