          translation: "There are two types of created beings in this world — the divine and the demonic. The divine has been described in detail. Now hear from Me about the demonic, O Partha.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna now sets up the FRAMEWORK for the rest of the chapter. Two types of beings in this world — DAIVA and ASURA. Divine and Demonic. And before anyone gets defensive — this is NOT about religion. This is not Hindu vs non-Hindu, believer vs atheist. This is about QUALITIES and TENDENCIES that exist in EVERY human being regardless of their background.\n\nThink of it as two OPERATING SYSTEMS running inside every person. The divine OS runs on compassion, truth, self-control, and humility. The demonic OS runs on ego, greed, anger, and hypocrisy. Every day, every moment, you are choosing which OS to boot up. Sometimes you run the divine one — you help someone without expecting anything back. Sometimes you run the demonic one — you lie to get ahead, you manipulate someone for personal gain.\n\nAnd notice Krishna says He has ALREADY described the divine in detail but now wants to focus on the DEMONIC. Why? Because we already KNOW what good looks like. We do not need a TED talk to understand that honesty, compassion, and kindness are good things. What we NEED is to understand the TRAPS — the subtle ways the demonic nature disguises itself as normal behavior. A doctor spends more time explaining the DISEASE than describing good health, because understanding the disease is what SAVES you.\n\nSo buckle up. Krishna is about to hold up a MIRROR, and what you see might be uncomfortable."
