          translation: "Persons of demonic nature do not know what to do and what to refrain from. Neither purity, nor proper conduct, nor truth is found in them.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna starts the DEEP DIVE into the demonic nature, and the first thing He identifies is the most FUNDAMENTAL problem — they do not know the difference between PRAVRITTI and NIVRITTI. They do not know what to DO and what to AVOID. They have lost the basic MORAL COMPASS.\n\nThis is not about intelligence. Some of the most demonic people in history were BRILLIANT. They could run empires, build corporations, manipulate millions. But they could not answer the basic question: 'Should I do this or should I not?' They had IQ but zero MORAL QUOTIENT. Think of that colleague who is technically excellent but has no idea that gossiping about others, taking credit for team work, and backstabbing people is WRONG. They genuinely do not see the problem. Their moral GPS is completely BROKEN.\n\nAnd then the three devastating diagnoses — NO PURITY, NO PROPER CONDUCT, NO TRUTH. Imagine a hospital where the doctors have no hygiene, no protocol, and no honesty. Would you trust that hospital? That is what a person without shaucha, achara, and satya is — a walking HAZARD ZONE.\n\nThe scariest part? These people often THRIVE in the short term. The world rewards cunning, celebrates aggression, promotes those who 'get things done' regardless of how. But Krishna is playing the LONG game. And in the long game, a life without purity, conduct, and truth is a building without a foundation — it WILL collapse, it is just a matter of WHEN."
