          modernInterpretation: "Krishna follows the PHILOSOPHY with the CONSEQUENCE. When someone adopts that nihilistic worldview from verse 8, what happens? They become NASHTATMANA — lost souls. Not lost in the sense of 'confused' but lost in the sense of 'DESTROYED from within.' Their very self has disintegrated. They have cut the connection to their own soul.\n\nALPA-BUDDHAYAH — small intellect. And this is DEVASTATING because these people often think they are the SMARTEST ones in the room. The person who says 'I have figured out that nothing matters' thinks he is a genius. Krishna calls him ALPA-BUDDHI — a small mind. Because REAL intelligence is not just about analyzing and deconstructing. Real intelligence BUILDS. Real intelligence finds MEANING. A child can break a toy. It takes an engineer to build one.\n\nUGRA-KARMANAH — they engage in TERRIBLE deeds. And KSHAYAYA JAGATAH — for the DESTRUCTION of the world. This is the trajectory. Step 1: adopt a worldview that says nothing matters. Step 2: lose your moral compass. Step 3: become capable of horrific actions because there is no internal brake system. Step 4: become an ENEMY of the world.\n\nEvery dictator, every corporate predator, every environmental destroyer follows this exact sequence. First they convince themselves that their actions do not have cosmic consequences. Then they do whatever serves their ego and desire. This verse is not ancient history — it is TONIGHT'S NEWS."
