          transliteration: "ātma-sambhāvitāḥ stabdhā dhana-māna-madānvitāḥ |\nyajante nāma-yajñais te dambhenāvidhi-pūrvakam ||17||",
          words: [
            { word: "आत्मसम्भाविताः", transliteration: "ātma-sambhāvitāḥ", meaning: "self-conceited" },
            { word: "स्तब्धाः", transliteration: "stabdhāḥ", meaning: "stubborn/obstinate" },
            { word: "धनमानमदान्विताः", transliteration: "dhana-māna-madānvitāḥ", meaning: "intoxicated by wealth and pride" },
            { word: "यजन्ते", transliteration: "yajante", meaning: "they perform sacrifice" },
            { word: "नामयज्ञैः", transliteration: "nāma-yajñaiḥ", meaning: "sacrifices in name only" },
            { word: "ते", transliteration: "te", meaning: "they" },
            { word: "दम्भेन", transliteration: "dambhena", meaning: "with ostentation/hypocrisy" },
            { word: "अविधिपूर्वकम्", transliteration: "avidhi-pūrvakam", meaning: "without following proper rules" }
          ],
          translation: "Self-conceited, stubborn, intoxicated by wealth and pride, they perform sacrifices in name only, with ostentation and without following proper rules.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna now describes how the demonic person interacts with RELIGION, and it is DEVASTATING. They DO perform religious rituals. They DO show up at temples. They DO organize yagnas and pujas. But it is all NAMA-YAJNA — sacrifice in NAME ONLY. The form is there, the substance is GONE. It is like a beautifully wrapped gift box with NOTHING inside.\n\nATMA-SAMBHAVITAH — self-conceited. They are their own biggest fans. They have given themselves a five-star review without anyone else's input. STABDHAH — rigid, stubborn, incapable of bending. They cannot learn because learning requires admitting you do not know something, and they already know EVERYTHING.\n\nDHANA-MANA-MADANVITAH — DRUNK on wealth and prestige. Not just wealthy and proud, but INTOXICATED by it. Wealth has gone to their head like alcohol goes to the brain. They cannot think straight anymore. Every decision is filtered through 'How does this affect my STATUS?'\n\nAnd their sacrifices? DAMBHENA — with OSTENTATION, with SHOW. AVIDHI-PURVAKAM — without following the actual RULES. This is the person who donates a crore to a temple and makes sure the plaque has their name in GOLD but cannot be bothered to treat their employees with basic dignity. It is the person who fasts on Ekadashi for Instagram but cheats on their taxes the next day. The RITUAL without the SPIRIT is not worship — it is THEATER. And God is not in the audience — God is backstage, watching the actor play a role that fools everyone except the Director."
