          translation: "Those hateful, cruel, and lowest of mankind, who are inauspicious, I perpetually cast into demonic wombs in the cycle of birth and death.",
          modernInterpretation: "This is one of the HARSHEST verses Krishna has ever spoken, and it needs to be understood carefully. He says — those who are cruel, hateful, and the LOWEST of humanity — KSHIPAMI AJASRAM — I REPEATEDLY hurl them into demonic births. Again and again and again.\n\nNow, this is NOT about God being VENGEFUL. This is about the LAW OF KARMA operating with mathematical precision. You do not get punished FOR your sins — you get punished BY your sins. A person filled with cruelty, hatred, and darkness does not need an external judge to sentence them. Their own nature DETERMINES their destination. A stone sinks in water not because the water is angry at it, but because that is what DENSITY does. Similarly, a soul heavy with demonic qualities SINKS into lower births not because God is punishing it, but because that is what SPIRITUAL GRAVITY does.\n\nNARADHAMAN — the lowest of mankind. This is not a casual insult. In the Gita's framework, being born as a human is a RARE and PRECIOUS opportunity. You have consciousness, free will, the ability to choose between dharma and adharma. When someone uses all of that MAGNIFICENT equipment to be cruel, hateful, and destructive — they have wasted the GREATEST opportunity in creation. They are like someone who wins a lottery and burns the check.\n\nAnd AJASRAM — perpetually, repeatedly. Not a one-time punishment but a CYCLE. Until the soul learns, it keeps repeating the class. The universe is incredibly PATIENT but also incredibly PERSISTENT. You will get infinite chances, but you will also face infinite consequences."
