          translation: "Arjuna said: Those who, setting aside the injunctions of scripture, perform worship endowed with faith — what is their position, O Krishna? Is it in goodness, passion, or ignorance?",
          modernInterpretation: "Welcome to Chapter 17 — SHRADDHATRAYA VIBHAGA YOGA — The Yoga of the Three Divisions of Faith. And Arjuna opens with an absolutely BRILLIANT question. He is basically asking: 'Krishna, what about people who DO have faith, who DO worship sincerely, but they are NOT following the scriptural rulebook? Where do THEY stand?'\n\nThis is SUCH a relevant question for our times. Think about it — how many people in your life are genuinely spiritual, genuinely devoted, but they are doing their OWN thing? They do not go to temples, they do not follow rituals, but they meditate in their own way, they pray in their own style, they have REAL faith. Are they sattvic? Rajasic? Tamasic? Where do they FIT?\n\nIt is like asking — if someone never went to IIT coaching but is a GENIUS at engineering, are they an engineer or not? If someone never went to culinary school but cooks INCREDIBLE food, are they a chef or not? Arjuna is essentially asking about the relationship between FORMAL structure and INNER conviction. Does the faith ITSELF matter, or does the METHOD of expressing it matter? And Krishna, as always, is about to give an answer that covers EVERY possible angle."
