          translation: "The Supreme Lord said: The faith of embodied beings is of three kinds, born of their own nature — sattvic (goodness), rajasic (passion), and tamasic (ignorance). Hear about it.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna IMMEDIATELY sets up the framework. Faith is not ONE thing — it is THREE things. And here is the key phrase: 'svabhāva-jā' — born of one's OWN NATURE. Your faith is not random. It is a PRODUCT of your accumulated tendencies, your past actions, your mental conditioning. You do not CHOOSE your faith in a vacuum — your faith REFLECTS who you already are.\n\nThis is EXACTLY like your taste in music. Nobody sits down and logically decides, 'I shall now enjoy classical music.' Your taste EMERGES from your nature. Someone with a refined, calm disposition gravitates toward classical. Someone energetic and ambitious gravitates toward hip-hop or EDM. Someone who just wants to zone out gravitates toward whatever requires zero mental engagement. Your PREFERENCES reveal your NATURE.\n\nSo Krishna is saying — do not just look at WHETHER someone has faith. Look at WHAT KIND of faith they have. Two people can both go to a temple. One goes seeking inner peace. Another goes seeking a promotion. A third goes because his mother dragged him there and he is scrolling Instagram during the aarti. SAME action, THREE completely different faiths behind it. And THAT is what determines the result."
