          translation: "Those in goodness worship the gods; those in passion worship yakshas and rakshasas; and others — those in ignorance — worship ghosts and spirits of the dead.",
          modernInterpretation: "Now Krishna gets SPECIFIC. He is saying — show me what you worship and I will tell you what guna dominates you. Sattvic people worship DEVAS — forces of light, knowledge, nature, divinity. They are drawn to things that ELEVATE. Rajasic people worship YAKSHAS and RAKSHASAS — beings of power, wealth, and domination. They are not seeking peace — they are seeking CONTROL. Tamasic people worship GHOSTS and SPIRITS — they are drawn to the dark, the dead, the occult.\n\nNow translate this to modern life. What do people WORSHIP today? The sattvic person worships KNOWLEDGE — they read books, seek wisdom, practice meditation, admire great teachers. The rajasic person worships SUCCESS and POWER — they follow billionaires on Twitter, read every hustle-culture book, worship at the altar of productivity and achievement. Nothing wrong with ambition, but when it becomes your GOD, it is rajasic faith.\n\nAnd the tamasic person? They worship DESTRUCTION and NEGATIVITY. They are drawn to doom-scrolling, conspiracy theories, toxic gossip, destructive habits. They do not build anything — they tear things down and call it entertainment. Your social media feed IS your temple. What you follow, what you consume, what you give your ATTENTION to — that is your worship. And it tells you EXACTLY which guna is running the show."
