          modernInterpretation: "Verses 5 and 6 go together, and Krishna is about to drop a BOMB. He starts describing people who do EXTREME spiritual practices — but for all the WRONG reasons. They are not prescribed by any legitimate tradition. They are GHORA — terrible, severe, extreme. And notice the motivation: DAMBHA (hypocrisy), AHANKARA (ego), KAMA (desire), and RAGA (attachment).\n\nYou have DEFINITELY seen these people. The person who posts their 40-day juice fast on Instagram every single day. The guy who does extreme yoga poses not for spiritual growth but for the PHOTO. People who turn spirituality into a PERFORMANCE — 'Look how spiritual I am, look how much I can endure, look at MY devotion.' The austerity is real, but the motivation is 100% ego.\n\nThis is the spiritual equivalent of TOXIC hustle culture. Just like there are people who destroy their health working 18 hours a day not because they love the work but because they want to POST about the grind — there are people who destroy their bodies through extreme fasts, sleep deprivation, and harsh practices not because they seek God, but because they seek ATTENTION. The pain is real. The suffering is real. But the PURPOSE is completely inverted. They are torturing themselves for likes and validation, not for liberation."
