          translation: "Senselessly torturing the elements of the body and also Me who dwells within — know them to be of demoniac resolve.",
          modernInterpretation: "HERE is the bomb. Krishna says — when you TORTURE your body through misguided austerities, you are not just hurting your physical elements. You are tormenting ME. Because 'antaḥ-śarīra-stham' — Krishna DWELLS within your body. The Paramatma, the Supreme Soul, is RIGHT THERE in your heart. So when you starve yourself to look spiritual, when you beat yourself up physically or mentally in the name of devotion, you are literally HURTING GOD.\n\nThis is REVOLUTIONARY. Most religions in the world have traditions of self-mortification — whipping yourself, extreme fasting, lying on beds of nails. Krishna calls this ASURIC — demoniac. Not divine. DEMONIAC. Because the body is a TEMPLE, and God lives IN it. You do not demolish a temple to prove your devotion to the deity inside it.\n\nThink of your body as a rented apartment where the LANDLORD also lives. If you trash the apartment — break the walls, flood the bathroom, set the kitchen on fire — you are not just damaging property. You are making your LANDLORD miserable. Krishna is that landlord. He says 'I am IN there with you. Stop destroying the house we BOTH live in.' This verse should be quoted every time someone promotes dangerous crash diets, extreme deprivation, or any form of self-harm disguised as spirituality. Your body is sacred because GOD is in it. Treat it accordingly."
