          modernInterpretation: "LOOK at this description. Sattvic food increases AYUH (lifespan), SATTVA (purity), BALA (strength), AROGYA (health), SUKHA (happiness), and PRITI (satisfaction). And the qualities? RASYA (juicy, flavorful), SNIGDHA (nourishing, with healthy fats), STHIRA (substantial, sustaining), HRIDYA (pleasing to the heart). This is not boring health food. This is DELICIOUS, WHOLESOME, SATISFYING food.\n\nForget every fad diet you have ever heard of. Krishna literally described the PERFECT diet 5000 years ago. Fresh fruits, wholesome grains, ghee, milk, nuts, fresh vegetables — food that makes you feel ALIVE after eating it, not sluggish. Food that you enjoy WHILE eating AND feel good AFTER eating. That post-meal feeling of contentment without heaviness? THAT is sattvic food.\n\nThe modern equivalent is simple. After eating sattvic food, you feel ENERGIZED. After a good home-cooked meal of dal, rice, sabzi, and roti with a little ghee — you feel satisfied, nourished, and ready to work or think clearly. Compare this to how you feel after a massive pizza or deep-fried binge. Your body KNOWS the difference. Sattvic food does not need a nutritionist to validate it — your own BODY gives you the feedback. If it makes you feel clean, clear, strong, and happy — it is sattvic. Period."
