          transliteration: "vidhi-hīnam asṛṣṭānnaṁ mantra-hīnam adakṣiṇam |\nśraddhā-virahitaṁ yajñaṁ tāmasaṁ paricakṣate ||13||",
          words: [
            { word: "विधिहीनम्", transliteration: "vidhi-hīnam", meaning: "without proper procedure" },
            { word: "असृष्टान्नम्", transliteration: "asṛṣṭa-annam", meaning: "without distribution of food" },
            { word: "मन्त्रहीनम्", transliteration: "mantra-hīnam", meaning: "without proper chanting" },
            { word: "अदक्षिणम्", transliteration: "adakṣiṇam", meaning: "without proper remuneration" },
            { word: "श्रद्धाविरहितम्", transliteration: "śraddhā-virahitam", meaning: "devoid of faith" },
            { word: "यज्ञम्", transliteration: "yajñam", meaning: "sacrifice" },
            { word: "तामसम्", transliteration: "tāmasam", meaning: "tamasic (in ignorance)" },
            { word: "परिचक्षते", transliteration: "paricakṣate", meaning: "they call/declare" }
          ],
          translation: "That sacrifice which is performed without regard for scriptural injunctions, without distribution of food, without proper hymns, without remuneration to the priests, and devoid of faith — is declared to be tamasic.",
          modernInterpretation: "The tamasic sacrifice is the EMPTY RITUAL. Five devastating deficiencies: no proper procedure (vidhi-hina), no sharing of food (asrishta-anna), no sacred mantras (mantra-hina), no proper dakshina or compensation (adakshina), and — the KILLER — no faith (shraddha-virahita).\n\nYou have been to these events. Someone is performing a puja, but nobody knows WHY they are doing it. The pandit is rushing through mantras nobody understands. No food is offered or shared — the most BASIC act of community and generosity is missing. The whole thing feels hollow, going through motions like a machine. Nobody's HEART is in it.\n\nThe modern equivalent is the company CSR event where everyone shows up because HR mandated it, nobody actually cares about the cause, the 'volunteers' spend more time taking selfies than working, and the moment it is over everyone goes back to exactly who they were before. Or the person who goes to temple mechanically every Tuesday because their parents told them to, stands there for ten minutes with their mind on their phone, puts a coin in the box, and leaves feeling nothing.\n\nThe KEY absence is SHRADDHA — faith. You can get the procedure wrong and still have a powerful sacrifice if your HEART is in it. But you can get every procedure PERFECT and still have a tamasic sacrifice if your heart is EMPTY. Faith is not optional seasoning — it is the MAIN INGREDIENT."
