          modernInterpretation: "Now Krishna unpacks SAT — the third and final component of the cosmic triad. SAT means TRUTH, REALITY, EXISTENCE, GOODNESS. It is used in two senses: SAD-BHAVE (the nature of reality — that which truly EXISTS) and SADHU-BHAVE (the nature of goodness — that which is genuinely VIRTUOUS). And it is applied to PRASHASTE KARMANI — praiseworthy, auspicious actions.\n\nSAT is the QUALITY CHECK of the spiritual life. When you say something is 'Sat,' you are declaring it to be REAL — not fake, not hollow, not pretend. It is the opposite of ASAT (unreal, false). In a world full of illusions, performances, and pretenses, SAT cuts through everything and asks: 'But is it TRUE? Is it REAL? Is it GOOD?'\n\nIn everyday Hindi, we still use SAT constantly. SATYA (truth), SATSANG (company of truth), SATVIK (pure), SANT (saint — one who embodies Sat). The word has permeated Indian culture so deeply that even people who have never read the Gita live by its echo.\n\nWhen Krishna says SAT is used for praiseworthy action, he is giving us a FILTER for all our deeds. Before any important action, ask: Is this SAT? Is it real, true, and good? If yes, proceed. If not, reconsider. It is the simplest ethical framework ever created — one syllable, three letters, infinite wisdom."
