          modernInterpretation: "Krishna now presents TWO schools of thought that were ACTIVELY debating each other in ancient India — and honestly, this debate is STILL happening today. One group says ALL action is inherently flawed. Every action, no matter how good, has SOME side effect, some karmic residue. So just STOP doing things. Become a monk. Sit in a cave. The other group says NO — certain actions like charity, sacrifice, and self-discipline are PURIFYING. You cannot just stop doing GOOD things because you are afraid of side effects.\n\nThis is EXACTLY like the modern debate about technology. One camp says social media is ALL bad — delete everything, go off-grid. The other camp says no, use it WISELY — for education, connection, positive content. Who is right? Krishna is about to give His verdict.\n\nWhat is beautiful here is that Krishna is not DISMISSING either view. He is acknowledging that INTELLIGENT people have landed on both sides of this argument. But He is setting up the audience to understand that the answer is more NUANCED than either extreme. Life is not about blanket rules — it is about WISDOM in application."
