          translation: "Acts of sacrifice, charity, and austerity should not be abandoned; they must indeed be performed. Sacrifice, charity, and austerity are purifying for the wise.",
          modernInterpretation: "HERE is Krishna's verdict, and it is CRYSTAL clear. Do NOT stop doing good things. Sacrifice, charity, and self-discipline are PURIFYING — even for people who are already wise. This is massive. Even the WISE need purification. It is like saying even the FITTEST athletes still need to work out. You never graduate from good karma.\n\nThink about the three things Krishna mentions: YAJNA (sacrifice/selfless service), DANA (giving/charity), and TAPAS (austerity/discipline). These are not optional nice-to-haves. These are MANDATORY. It is like saying exercise, healthy eating, and sleep are non-negotiable for physical health. You cannot skip them just because you have 'evolved beyond' them.\n\nThe people who say 'I am so spiritual I do not need to DO anything' — Krishna is directly refuting that nonsense here. True spirituality is not about INACTION. It is about action done with the RIGHT spirit. A CEO who donates to charity, a teacher who mentors without expecting anything, a parent who sacrifices for their child — these people are not binding themselves with karma. They are PURIFYING themselves through karma. And Krishna says this with the word 'EVA' — INDEED, CERTAINLY, WITHOUT DOUBT. No ambiguity."
