          modernInterpretation: "And HERE is the GOLD STANDARD. Sattvic tyaga. You do what needs to be done BECAUSE it needs to be done. Not for reward, not for recognition, not for comfort — simply because it is the RIGHT thing to do. And while doing it, you drop attachment to both the ACTION and the RESULT.\n\nThis is the doctor who treats patients because healing people is their DHARMA — not because of the fee. This is the soldier who defends the border because it is their DUTY — not because they want a medal. This is the mother who wakes up at 5 AM for her children because that is what LOVE looks like — not because she expects gratitude.\n\nNotice the word KARYAM — 'it must be done.' There is a beautiful simplicity here. You do not need complex philosophical justification. You do not need motivation speeches or vision boards. You simply look at what needs to be done, and you DO it. No drama, no attachment, no anxiety about outcomes. This is the state of a truly FREE person — someone who acts from DUTY and LOVE, not from desire and fear. Krishna considers this the HIGHEST form of renunciation. You have not renounced ACTION — you have renounced SELFISHNESS in action. And THAT is the entire teaching of the Gita in a single verse."
