          modernInterpretation: "What does a truly sattvic person LOOK like in daily life? Krishna gives us the portrait here. They do not HATE the hard parts of their job, and they do not get ADDICTED to the easy parts. They take the bitter medicine and the sweet dessert with the SAME equanimity.\n\nImagine a project manager who handles both the exciting product launches AND the boring compliance paperwork with the same level of engagement. No sighing when the unpleasant email comes in, no excessive celebration when the bonus arrives. They are STEADY. They are what Krishna calls MEDHAVI — truly intelligent. Not book-smart, but LIFE-smart.\n\nAnd the most powerful word here is CHHINNA-SAMSHAYAH — their doubts are DESTROYED. Not suppressed, not managed — DESTROYED. They are not second-guessing themselves. They are not wondering 'should I be doing something else with my life?' They have found their CENTER, and from that center, they engage with EVERYTHING — pleasant or unpleasant — with equal grace. This is not emotional numbness. This is emotional MASTERY. The difference is like the difference between a person who cannot feel the rain and a person who dances in it."
