          modernInterpretation: "Krishna reveals the KARMIC mathematics here. Every action you do while ATTACHED to results creates a karmic bill — and that bill comes in three flavors: BAD results (suffering), GOOD results (temporary pleasure), and MIXED results (a complicated blend of both). And this bill does not expire when you die — it carries forward.\n\nThink of it like a CREDIT SCORE that follows you across lifetimes. Every desire-driven action adds a transaction. Some boost your score, some crash it, some do a bit of both. But the person who has truly renounced — who acts without attachment to results — they have essentially achieved a ZERO-BALANCE KARMA ACCOUNT. No new transactions being recorded. No bills accumulating.\n\nThis is the ultimate FREEDOM. Most people are terrified of death because they sense, even subconsciously, that unresolved karma is waiting on the other side. But the true sannyasi, the one who has genuinely given up attachment to fruits — they face death the way you face closing a tab on your browser. Nothing lost, nothing pending, nothing unresolved. They are DONE. And this is why Krishna has been hammering this message for 18 chapters — because the stakes are not just about THIS life. They are about EVERY life that follows."
