          translation: "That fortitude by which a person of poor understanding does not let go of excessive sleep, fear, grief, depression, and intoxication — that, O Partha, is tamasic.",
          modernInterpretation: "TAMASIC fortitude — and this is the most TRAGIC form of determination. This person IS stubborn. They DO hold on tenaciously. But what are they holding onto? SLEEP (escapism), BHAYA (fear), SHOKA (grief), VISHADA (depression), and MADA (intoxication/arrogance). They are DETERMINED to stay STUCK.\n\nThis is the person who CLINGS to their sadness like it is their identity. Who REFUSES to let go of past trauma — not because healing is happening, but because the trauma has become their comfort zone. Who is DEVOTED to their addictions. Who is COMMITTED to their fears. They have incredible PERSISTENCE — but in the WRONG direction.\n\nKrishna calls this person DURMEDHA — of poor understanding. They have INVESTED their willpower into maintaining their prison. It is like using a powerful lock — not to protect your valuables, but to lock yourself INSIDE a burning building. The capacity for determination is THERE, but it is pointed at exactly the wrong things.\n\nWe all know people who are WORLD-CLASS at holding grudges, maintaining addictions, nurturing anxieties, and avoiding growth. That takes EFFORT. That takes FORTITUDE. But it is tamasic fortitude — the tragic waste of human willpower on self-destruction. If they could REDIRECT even 10% of that stubborn energy toward positive growth, their lives would transform overnight."
