          translation: "That happiness which arises from the contact of senses with sense objects, which is like nectar in the beginning but like poison in the end — that is declared to be rajasic happiness.",
          modernInterpretation: "The EXACT OPPOSITE of sattvic happiness. Rajasic happiness is AMRITOPAMAM in the beginning — it TASTES like nectar when you first experience it — but becomes VISHAM, pure POISON, in the end.\n\nThe first bite of junk food — AMAZING. The obesity, diabetes, and heart disease that follow years of it — POISON. The first drink of alcohol — euphoric. The addiction, broken relationships, and liver damage — POISON. The first dopamine hit of social media validation — INTOXICATING. The anxiety, comparison, and self-worth destruction — POISON. The first rush of a new romantic affair — electrifying. The guilt, broken trust, and shattered families — POISON.\n\nKrishna identifies the SOURCE: VISHAYA-INDRIYA-SAMYOGA — the contact of SENSES with SENSE OBJECTS. This happiness is essentially a CHEMICAL REACTION between your senses and external stimuli. Like striking a match — bright flame instantly, but it BURNS OUT and burns your fingers. And each time, you need MORE of the stimulus to get the SAME level of happiness. This is literally the mechanism of ADDICTION, described 5,000 years before neuroscience named it.\n\nPut verses 37 and 38 side by side and you have the COMPLETE MAP of human pleasure. Sattvic: bitter start, sweet forever. Rajasic: sweet start, bitter forever. CHOOSE WISELY."
