          translation: "By worshipping through one's own duty Him from whom all beings originate and by whom all this is pervaded, a person attains perfection.",
          modernInterpretation: "This verse contains one of the most REVOLUTIONARY ideas in spiritual history: YOUR WORK IS YOUR WORSHIP. SvaKARMANA tam ABHYARCHYA — by worshipping HIM through YOUR OWN DUTY. You do not need a temple. You do not need rituals. You do not need to leave your job and go to an ashram. Your JOB is your ASHRAM. Your WORK is your PUJA.\n\nThe doctor who heals with total devotion is worshipping God through medicine. The teacher who teaches with full heart is worshipping God through education. The farmer who grows food with care is worshipping God through agriculture. The coder who writes clean, efficient code with integrity is worshipping God through technology.\n\nThis democratizes spirituality COMPLETELY. You do not need special qualifications to worship God. You do not need to be born in a particular family. You do not need a specific language or scripture. You need exactly ONE thing: do YOUR work with the awareness that it is an offering to the DIVINE who pervades everything.\n\nThe phrase YENA SARVAM IDAM TATAM — 'by whom all this is pervaded' — reminds us that God is not sitting somewhere far away waiting for our prayers. God IS the pervading presence in everything. So when you serve a customer, you are serving God. When you clean a floor, you are cleaning God's floor. When you write code, you are writing in God's language. EVERYTHING becomes sacred when seen through this lens."
