          translation: "Dwelling in solitude, eating lightly, controlling speech, body, and mind, constantly devoted to meditation, and taking refuge in dispassion —",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna continues the path description with LIFESTYLE practices. VIVIKTA-SEVI — seeking SOLITUDE. Not permanent isolation, but regular time ALONE with yourself. In our hyperconnected world where you are never truly alone — always on WhatsApp, always on social media — this is RADICAL advice. The mind needs SPACE to process, reflect, and settle.\n\nLAGHV-ASHI — eating LIGHTLY. Not fasting, not feasting — LIGHT eating. Your body runs better on less fuel than you think. The post-lunch food coma that kills your productivity? That is HEAVY eating destroying your clarity.\n\nYATA-VAK-KAYA-MANASA — controlling SPEECH, BODY, and MIND. Three levels of discipline, listed in order of increasing difficulty. Controlling your body (not going where you should not) is the easiest. Controlling your speech (not saying what you should not) is harder. Controlling your MIND (not thinking what you should not) is the HARDEST. But all three are needed.\n\nDHYANA-YOGA-PARA — devoted to MEDITATION constantly. Not just 20 minutes in the morning. A CONSTANT meditative awareness. And VAIRAGYA — dispassion. Not hatred of the world, but a GENTLE non-clinging. Like holding a bird in your open palm — present, but not grasping."
