          transliteration: "sarva-karmāṇy api sadā kurvāṇo mad-vyapāśrayaḥ |\nmat-prasādād avāpnoti śāśvataṁ padam avyayam ||56||",
          words: [
            { word: "सर्वकर्माणि", transliteration: "sarva-karmāṇi", meaning: "all actions" },
            { word: "अपि", transliteration: "api", meaning: "even" },
            { word: "सदा", transliteration: "sadā", meaning: "always" },
            { word: "कुर्वाणः", transliteration: "kurvāṇaḥ", meaning: "performing" },
            { word: "मद्व्यपाश्रयः", transliteration: "mad-vyapāśrayaḥ", meaning: "taking refuge in Me" },
            { word: "मत्प्रसादात्", transliteration: "mat-prasādāt", meaning: "by My grace" },
            { word: "अवाप्नोति", transliteration: "avāpnoti", meaning: "attains" },
            { word: "शाश्वतम्", transliteration: "śāśvatam", meaning: "eternal" },
            { word: "पदम्", transliteration: "padam", meaning: "abode/state" },
            { word: "अव्ययम्", transliteration: "avyayam", meaning: "imperishable" }
          ],
          translation: "Always performing all actions, but taking refuge in Me, one attains by My grace the eternal, imperishable abode.",
          modernInterpretation: "This verse DEMOLISHES the myth that you need to STOP working to achieve spiritual liberation. SARVA-KARMANI API SADA KURVANAH — ALWAYS performing ALL actions. You do not stop. You do not retire to a cave. You keep WORKING. But with one CRUCIAL addition: MAD-VYAPASHRAYAH — taking REFUGE in Me.\n\nAnd then the GAME-CHANGER: MAT-PRASADAT — by MY GRACE. Not by your effort alone. Not by your meditation alone. Not by your knowledge alone. By GRACE. All your effort, all your devotion, all your discipline — they QUALIFY you. But the final step? That is GRACE. You cannot EARN your way into the eternal. Grace must LIFT you there.\n\nThis is like a rocket launch. The rocket needs enormous fuel (your effort), precise engineering (your discipline), perfect trajectory (your wisdom). But at a certain point, you leave the atmosphere and GRAVITY itself changes — you enter a DIFFERENT realm where the old rules do not apply. That transition point is grace.\n\nSHASHVATAM PADAM AVYAYAM — the ETERNAL, IMPERISHABLE state. Not temporary heaven. Not short-term bliss. PERMANENT. FOREVER. And you reach it not by abandoning life but by living life with GOD as your refuge. This is the most HOPEFUL teaching in the Gita — that liberation is available to EVERYONE, in EVERY condition, doing ANY work, as long as they take refuge in the Divine."
