          translation: "Mentally surrendering all actions to Me, regarding Me as the Supreme, taking refuge in the yoga of intellect — fix your mind on Me constantly.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna gives a DIRECT instruction — the most PRACTICAL directive in the Gita. Four things to do SIMULTANEOUSLY: 1) CETASA SARVA-KARMANI MAYI SANNYASYA — mentally surrender ALL your actions to God (not physically stopping, but mentally OFFERING). 2) MAT-PARAH — hold God as the SUPREME goal (not money, not fame, not even enlightenment as an intellectual concept — GOD). 3) BUDDHI-YOGAM UPASHRITYA — take shelter in the YOGA OF INTELLECT (use your discriminating intelligence to stay connected). 4) MAC-CHITTAH SATATAM BHAVA — keep your mind CONSTANTLY on God.\n\nThis is like a TASK MANAGER running in the background of your phone. While you run all your daily apps — work, family, social — there is a CONSTANT background process running: awareness of God. You do not stop your work to pray. You PRAY through your work. You do not close your apps to think of God. You think of God WHILE running your apps.\n\nThe word SATATAM — CONSTANTLY — is key. Not occasionally. Not on weekends. Not just during festivals. ALWAYS. This is the most demanding instruction Krishna gives, and also the most TRANSFORMATIVE. Because when your mind is constantly oriented toward the Divine, EVERY action becomes worship, EVERY moment becomes meditation, and EVERY experience becomes a step toward liberation."
