          translation: "If, taking refuge in your ego, you think 'I will not fight' — that resolve is false. Your own nature will compel you.",
          modernInterpretation: "Krishna delivers a PSYCHOLOGICAL truth bomb. He tells Arjuna: your decision NOT to fight is itself an act of EGO, not humility. You THINK you are being noble by refusing to fight. But that refusal is MITHYA — FALSE, ILLUSORY. Your PRAKRUTI — your warrior nature — will FORCE you to fight eventually.\n\nThis is SO relevant to modern life. The person who says 'I am going to quit my stressful corporate job and live a simple life' — but they have the temperament of a competitor, a builder, a leader. They WILL go back. Their nature will DRAG them back. The artist who says 'I am done with art, it is too painful' — but they DREAM in colors and shapes. They WILL create again. You cannot suppress your fundamental nature forever.\n\nKrishna is saying: You can PRETEND to be someone you are not, but your PRAKRITI — your inborn nature — is STRONGER than your pretense. A lion cannot decide to be a sheep. A river cannot decide to stop flowing. You are a WARRIOR, Arjuna. Your kshatriya nature will not let you sit this out. So instead of fighting your nature AND the war, just ALIGN with your nature and fight the war with CLARITY.\n\nThis is the ultimate argument against false renunciation: your nature is not something you can overrule with ego. Your nature is what you ARE."
