          translation: "The Supreme Lord dwells in the hearts of all beings, O Arjuna, causing all beings — mounted on the machine (of the body) — to revolve through Maya.",
          modernInterpretation: "One of the most PROFOUND verses in the entire Gita. God is not in a temple. God is not in heaven. God is in YOUR HEART — HRD-DESHE. In the heart of EVERY being. The saint and the sinner. The human and the ant. The friend and the enemy. God sits in the HEART of each one.\n\nAnd the IMAGE Krishna uses is extraordinary: YANTRA-ARUDHANI — beings are mounted on a YANTRA, a MACHINE. Your body is a MACHINE, and you are riding it. Like a passenger on a merry-go-round. BHRAMAYAN — God causes these machines to REVOLVE, to go round and round, through MAYA — the cosmic illusion.\n\nThink about it — your body IS a machine. It has mechanical parts (bones, joints), an electrical system (nervous system), a plumbing system (circulatory system), a processing unit (brain), and sensory inputs (eyes, ears). You are RIDING this biological machine through life, and the machine is being operated by a force much BIGGER than you.\n\nThis verse simultaneously HUMBLES you (you are not the master — you are a passenger on a machine) and COMFORTS you (the driver is GOD, sitting in your very heart). You are never alone. You are never truly lost. The Supreme Intelligence that created the universe is sitting RIGHT INSIDE YOU, guiding the machine of your life. The only question is: will you LISTEN to the driver, or will you keep grabbing at the steering wheel?"
