          modernInterpretation: "Krishna says something EXTRAORDINARY here — 'Do as you WISH.' After 18 chapters of teaching, after showing the Universal Form, after explaining every path to liberation — He does not COMMAND. He does not threaten. He says — 'Think about it. Then do whatever YOU want.'\n\nThis is the ultimate respect for FREE WILL. God teaches, guides, reveals, loves — but does not FORCE. The choice is always YOURS. No spiritual blackmail. No 'believe or burn.' Just — here is the truth. Now choose.\n\nThis makes the Gita fundamentally DIFFERENT from any authoritarian teaching. Krishna is the ultimate teacher because He gives you ALL the information and then STEPS BACK. The decision to act is yours. The responsibility is yours. The freedom is yours."
