          modernInterpretation: "After giving the ULTIMATE teaching, Krishna adds a WARNING LABEL. Do not share this with four types of people: those without discipline (atapaska), those without devotion (abhakta), those who do not want to listen (aśuśrūṣu), and those who are envious of God (abhyasūyati).\n\nThis is not elitism — it is PROTECTION. Sacred knowledge in the wrong hands is not just wasted — it is dangerous. Like giving a nuclear reactor manual to someone who hates physics. The knowledge will either be MOCKED or MISUSED.\n\nThe Gita is for the SINCERE seeker. The one who has at least a spark of discipline, a flicker of devotion, a genuine desire to listen, and no enmity toward the Divine. If you are reading this — you qualify."
